name: Delaware State Police Museum
address: 1425 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Our son is very interested in law enforcement and this was a cool place to visit. You don't need a lot of time to go through the exhibits. It's free to get in and the kids had fun exploring the different parts of the museum. It has about 2 large rooms housing various police equipment and paraphernalia from decades past. The bonus was that it's only 15 min from the Air Mobility Command Museum so we did both I'm one day.
An excellent history of Deleware State Troopers.  All sorts of equipment uniforms guns and even vehicles.  Well laid out and includes some interactive displays
What a wonderful tribute to our Delaware State Troopers. The museum is outstanding. Everyone should spend some time there and thank our police for their  dedication.
This museum is free and definitely worth the visit. Some of the interactive items are broken, but it doesn't take away from the allure.
This was great place to visit. Very interesting. We had lots if fun

name: Dover International Speedway
address: 1131 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Went for a private tour on a rainy Monday morning. Wasn't expecting much but boy I was wrong! We had a blast. Our tour guide told us in great detail the story of the speedway, he showed us the different areas and even took us for a lap on the track in his own car, we also walked part of the track and saw the high angle that thing has. We also went to the media room and saw how everything there works on race day. If you love Nascar or car racing in general this is a must.

Drinks and food 2 expensive.  Mainly the band club. Lower the drink prices. The patrons will get out of there gambling chair and watch the entertainment. Food is awesome but the casino ask the restaurants the pay to much in rental fees. My understanding is greed. Spend more as a patron and pay more as a food service along with any business who wants business in there casino. Just because you provide a service in a casino. Dont give the casinos the right to charge more outrageous rental space to the food beverage and other businesses providers. You attract more businesses if you keep prices fair. But casinos are all about gr÷ed. The division sign is to prove is it worth it.

Not every pull of the lever leads to a win. I enjoyed this "play place ". Very well lit. It didn't feel like they tried to cram as many machines and people as they could in there. AND I took my money back home with me! WINNING!!
Had a fun time there and stayed in a room for the evening.  Nice accommodations.  Big selection of slots. Going again this month for my anniversary.  Wish me luck 👌

This speedway is pretty fantastic and will make for an awesome day of NASCAR. The parking is expansive and yes, you may need to walk a distance, but it’s worth it. For an event, there usually are food trucks and activities for customers. The stadium seating is like any other, so if you suffer from back pain, I would bring a cushion. The bathrooms are well maintained.

name: Air Mobility Command Museum
address: 1301 Heritage Rd, Dover AFB, DE 19902, USA
reviews: My boyfriend and I have been wanting to come here for awhile.  For our Valentine's weekend I planned the trip and didn't tell him.  When we got there,  we both were so excited as we both love planes.  We enjoyed the museum greatly!  It was amazing to think that we were in planes that were used so long ago.  The history and knowledge were incredible.  ED R. was our tour guide and he was excellent (and funny).  This was one of the greatest adventures we've done and it was FREE! We can't wait to go back to see more!

I went here for father’s day as my dad loves aviation history. There is an inside and outside part to the museum, both offering large collections of planes to look at. Inside, a guide kindly let us into one of the planes and taught us about the history of the plane as well as it’s role in the war and how it came to the museum. Outside, there are several planes that you can go in and explore. Easy day trip if you’re in the area!

What a small but mighty gem! The volunteers are just as much a part of the museum as the dozens of historic planes. They live and love the work they do and so many of them are veterans with a passion to share stories. The personnel of their own accord kindly showed me and a friend around the place and through different planes, answering questions expertly. 

The curators left finges of sass and humor throughout that really just makes an enjoyable experience. It was very worth the two-hour drive from DC/NOVA and I would love to come back on their monthly Saturday event where all 40+ planes are opened to enter!

LOVED coming here. Kevin really made our visit special and took us round lots of planes, including photos and detailed accounts of the history of some of the planes there. There's an impressive array of sites, as well as simulators! 
Definitely plan on returning with more time and family. Thank you Kevin!

Great place to go for families to learn about our history. Our four kids loved all of the airplanes and interactive stations. They especially loved the flight simulator where they got to land an airplane themselves and "earn their wings" sticker 😁👍

name: Delaware Agricultural Museum
address: 866 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Nice little museum highlighting Delaware's agricultural history. Run by caring people and volunteers. I was there for A Farmer's Christmas,  an annual event. If you're wanting bright, shiny and upscale, this isn't that type of place. But if you're interested in learning about the agricultural  history of the state, this is a wonderful place to visit. The displays and facilities are carefully and thoughtfully maintained by dedicated staff and volunteers. This museum is small town America at best.

Nice place to go spend a Summer day to keep the kids occupied.  There is not a lot of stuff they can touch and play with inside so depending on how young your kids are, it might not be ideal.  My girls loved feeding the pig who is super social and calm.  You also can actually go into the chickens little fenced in coop area and feed them as well.  My daughter ended up with chicken poop all over her but it made for a nice laugh after her brief meltdown lol.  The woman who was working there was SUPER nice.  The school house bell is fun to ring for the kids too.  They enjoy exploring the historic village outside.

Excellent museum showing early farm life in Delaware.   Includes some historic buildings that have been brought to the property.  Lots of history of local folks who helped Delaware to grow and prosper.

Bought back a lot of fun memories.  Watching my Uncle  Jim and his family working on their farms as a child in up State New York.  Learned about more of the process I didn't know about as well
  Very friendly help full staff
Wonderful place to visit. A lot of history

name: John Dickinson Plantation
address: 340 Kitts Hummock Rd, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: My husband and I took their tour on 2/19/20.  John Dickinson was a fascinating, impressive and extremely accomplished man.  He is well worth learning about.  The house and grounds are so interesting.  We love learning about peoples' everyday lives from that period.  Our guide, Chris, was knowledgeable and interesting.  He welcomed all our questions (and we had  many).  He answered all of them and we learned so much.  The video beforehand was quite useful.   The ladies at the Welcome Center were also full of information about John Dickinson and his life.
I grew up in Delaware but had never been here for a tour.  It was an awesome tour.  The tour guides were terrific especially young Tyler.
Been there twice. Once with school and the other time with my fiancée. It is free and they do accept donations. It is beautiful. Mostly all the info is correct. They do events.

The guides were very knowledgeable and wonderful.  However i wish they would recomend an age that children should be to enjoy things like this.  The children were very behaved but pretty much board to death.

Immerse in Delaware and American history while visiting this well preserved plantation. The whole visit with the house tour doesn't take more than an hour and a half. Definitely watch the video in the barn.

name: Johnson Victrola Museum
address: 375 S New St, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Very interesting, free museum in Dover. Full of some incredible old phonographs and some very helpful and insightful staff members. Definitely worth a stop and it doesn't take long to see all it has to offer. Ask for a demonstration of some of the machines, you won't regret it!
Guides were very friendly and knowledgeable and would answer questions with enthusiasm. We very much enjoyed are vist.

This place is amazing. To have all of those old Victrolas, and records, that are over 100 years old, and it all still work, simply amazing. What really blew my mind was how that 100+ yo record sounded as good as anything in this digital age, stunning! You have really got to stop and visit this place.

This was such a fantastic museum, and I'd have to say the best "museum" experience I've had in a long time! The guide gave lots of extra information and stories compared to if I had gone through the museum on my own. She played some records on some of the older pieces they had, and it was enchanting. I'd go back in a heart beat!
Awesome victrola history! Outgoing staff. Could not give 5 stars because there is no elevator/ ramp to reach the 2nd floor 🤔😣

name: The Old State House
address: 25 The Green, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: This is a tremendously interesting historical building. The fantastic tour guides were full of knowledge and resources. We really came away with a fantastic appreciation for the historical value that the old state house is in its current state as a museum. From the realistic displays to the replica setup. It was a fabulous experience for the entire group of people that we were traveling with.
This place is worth visiting. It is maintained very well. A lot of history to be seen.
This is a beautiful building.  The staff were very friendly and gave a great tour.
Great little building full of history and both the guides were excellent, providing details and stories

Stopped in for a tour and was so impressed by the young woman who gave us a tour! The building itself is magnificent, but the enthusiasm and knowledgeability of the tour guide made the experience so incredible. Tours are offered on demand as soon as you walk in, so no need to schedule a time or come in on the hour (however, the walking tour, which is separate from the state house tour, leaves on the hour). Overall I had a great time here and would recommend it to anyone! (No public restrooms in the building, but there is one available nearby at the art museum. Plenty is parking available both in front of the state house itself and on the side streets nearby.)

name: Biggs Museum of American Art
address: 406 Federal St, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: It is a pretty small museum and there isn't much to see there.  It has a nice layout.  It will take less than an hour to go through all 3 floors.

I had never heard of this place, but when my colleague suggested, I had to go
 My husband and I took a Saturday to wander around a couple of museums in Dover. By far, the Biggs Museum was our favorite.  There was an Audobon exhibit when we were there along with pagers from children's books. I intend to go back soon. The exhibits change often. I'm not sure of the entrance price as I got us a Groupon, but didn't need it. Pro tip: The first Saturday of every month is free
Nice little local museum. Sometimes they have really interesting rotating exhibits too. The first Saturday of the month is always free too, which is nice.
This is a great place to see historical relics of the area as well as modern artists.

An absolute gem of a museum in the heart of Dover. I became a member shortly after moving to the Dover area and am extremely pleased by the first class presentations at this modestly sized museum. The staff are extremely knowledgeable and I am amazed at the range of exhibits that they put on throughout the year. I particularly enjoy the exhibitions with local artists.

name: Silver Lake Park
address: Washington St, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Still my favorite place to visit. As a child we could swim in the lake but there was more sand and lots of swings. Things have changed; absolutely swimming, the swings that made you feel like you were going into the lake are no longer there, and no life guard stands but it was still nice to revisit my childhood playground. The picnic tables are still there!

Great spot to spend a day with family or friends.
A good source of fish brings predators here and we saw Bald Eagle , seagull .
Great place to picnic, fish and if they ever open up the beach for swimming again that would even be better, the water even was actually pretty clean!! The family had a great time!!
It was nice and quiet to take my dog for a walk. For as hot as it's been, the dog park had quite a few people walking their furry babies too.

Always a wonderful place to unwine,  people watch, bird watch , duck an geese watch an to take your dogs for a walk. Very relaxing an safe. You can even have a picnic,  go fishing or play volleyball ball.

name: Spence's Bazaar & Auction
address: 550 S New St, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: Great experience! My partner loves going and bidding on on new treasures from others junk! Lol. The bids are reasonable. You don't have to be rich to join in on the fun. He got this little exercise trampoline (minus the dog) along w other stuff for $5 or $6. Auction starts at 12:30 pm on days they're open. Go and have good time! Oh, the food is awesome also. Amish is mainly vendors that sell it and they know what they're doing! There's also shopping in the back. Anything from clothes to personal hygiene products for reasonable prices.

Super crowded and busy, but it is expected when you visit during lunch time. The pretzel booth is definitely a must-try. There's  plenty of homemade goods. Most of the items are sold and made by either Amish people or Mennonites. You will see most with thwir traditional garments as they cook and sell their items.

Same as it was when I came 35 years ago. I call them the original amazon. Great deals you can catch some very good merchandise during the auction. If you need some quick cash minus all the Haggling bring your treasures log them with office  and let Spencers sell all your stuff. 2 hours later come collect your cash. Also the Farmers market has some awesome food. Homemade Ice cream cakes and pies. Hot food made by Amish very good.
Nice outing Tuesday Friday auction days

Spence's Bazaar has been a WONDERFUL place to visit FOR MORE YEARS THAN I CAN COUNT!!!  I sojourn there as often as I possibly can!  

The Amish foods (donuts, meats, ice creams, desserts, candies, etc., etc.,) are SUPER EXCELLENT ~ as expected!!!  

I've  purchased more foods, fruits, vegetables; tomato/pepper plants; fresh, LARGE strawberries; jewelry, hair jewelry/items; clothing and shoes [new and used]; comforters, ALTOGETHER CAPTIVATING blankets and SO, SO, SO MANY OTHER NOVELTY ITEMS at Spence's Bazaar than I can possibly EVER COUNT! 

Everyone should visit Spence's.  Just ONE TRIP to that place and you'll be captivated for life.  My hubby and I went there when we were just married 38 years ago, and we've remained faithful, loyal patrons ever since. We've known some of the vendors for many, many years (and some of them are truly WONDERFUL, AMAZING, AWESOME PEOPLE).  

It was burned down by some arsonist juveniles a number of years ago and the owners were uncertain of rebuilding; however, the merchants of Dover, DE, (possibly some of the vendors themselves《?》) and/or citizens got together and decided that THIS PLACE was too important ~ REPEAT, TOO CRITICAL TO LOSE, so they got together and it was rebuilt (Who did it exactly?  I do NOT KNOW).  I won't presume and/or pretend that I do!

There are many different vendors who rely on sales from Spence's. Those of us who are clients rely on it/them as well.  What an AWESOME PLACE TO VISIT!!! I highly recommend it to EVERYONE.  It's truly phenomenal.
Very crowded at lunch time. Breakfast seems to be the favorite. The baked goods are delicious and so are the pretzels. Some places take cash only so hit the ATM to be safe before going.

name: First State Heritage Park's John Bell House
address: 43 The Green, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: A great free walking tour about the history of the Green & Dover. The interpreter was wearing colonial clothing. The tour is less than a hour
Need to come to on the 1st Saturday of every month. You learn so much

This is the place you go to for a free guided tour of the Dover historic district. The guides dress in 18th century (?) garb and they take you out on a 45 minute walking tour of the square. 

Our guide (I believe her name was Anne?) was amazing! The whole tour was very captivating and it was evident that our guide was very passionate about Delaware history. We went there on a Wednesday afternoon, and my wife and I were there only ones there. The whole tour is wheelchair accessible, although, you have to be careful at certain points due to uneven surfaces.

On the whole, I would strongly recommend taking the tour. Learnt a lot about Delaware history in those 45 minutes.
What a great piece of Delaware history. The staff was so nice and knowledgeable!
Had a free tour of historic Dover that left from the Bell house. Guide was awesome and very knowledgeable. Highly recommend it

name: Brecknock County Park
address: 80 Old Camden Rd, Camden, DE 19934, USA
reviews:
Great amenities such as a huge playground for the kiddies and nicely appointed horseshoe pits. Really nice walking trail (1 mile loop) good for the pups. 
If you do walk your dog here, please be considerate and clean up behind your furry friend. Trail is frequented by families with kids and nobody wants to be dodging dog mess as you go. Enjoy this nice, clean park.

Possibly the best park in the Dover area. Great place to kick back with the kids, or let them run wild and still have good vision from most areas. The picnic area is adequate and clean. The location has public restrooms that are usually clean. The walk path is amazing.
Very nice walking path through the woods and perimeter of park. Very nice Naturist Center with knowledgeable and personable Staff.

I walk here usually once a week after my yoga and gym workout at the YMCA. I love to experience the different seasons from fall winter and summer and the wildlife that is along the trails. Always friendly people walking. Young people jogging and people walking their dogs. A good place to unwind
Great park to exercise in or take the child to play in.  Only downside is,  the 1 mile path isn't blacktop for those who wanna run.  But otherwise, great exercise and fun place for the kids

name: First State Heritage Park
address: 102 S State St, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Great historical tours.
Very nice tour. Well kept.

name: Schutte Park
address: 10 Electric Ave, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: Great Park very quiet kids were able to run around and play and enjoy themselves without having to bump into 3 million children it was nice to be able to enjoy the weather and watch the kids have lots of fun we were able to walk through the trails in the back without it being all wet really great small park for when you want to spend quality time with your kids
Large beautiful( good for football an baseball) picnic  tables available,  good walking trails, friendly environment  an bathroom available both inside Recreation center an outdoor
Two large playscapes. One for older kids 5+ and one for younger kids. I didnt explore much outside the playground area. Everything looked clean and well maintained.

Volunteered for the veterans stand down and being a veteran myself I also enjoyed the booths.  Had an opportunity to explore the area and I will go back.  Taking the grandkids next time as the playground is huge and walking areas are beautiful.
A Nice Place 2 Fly!

name: Woodburn: Governor's House
address: 151 Kings Hwy SW, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews:
The most interesting thing about the Governor's Mansion is the fact that it is so accessible! If the governor is not present, you can walk by the house and in the governor's gardens. The perks to living in such a small state. 

The mansion itself is in Georgian style, and it is so inconspicuous that unless there was a sign that said "Governor's Mansion," you would probably just assume that it was a cool old house. The Mansion is on the National Register of Historic Places, so drive by, snap a picture, and see if you can stroll by the gardens.
Food is good, price is great an the place has a relaxing feel of spring time

I e-mailed twice inquiring about a tour. No response. I show up in person during the posted open hours and it's closed up. 3 employees outside completely ignored me. Very disappointing. The gardens are lovely, though.
Beautiful from the outside never been inside though
This place is really beautiful you really have to go walk through and see it

name: Bombay Hook National Wildlife Refuge
address: 2591 Whitehall Neck Rd, Smyrna, DE 19977, USA
reviews: Great area to observe migrating shorebirds ducks and geese.  This is mainly a driving refuge with only limited hiking available.  A nice reception building with small exhibits and clean bathrooms.  Easy to navigate on the roads.  A definitely great place for birdwatchers and anyone who enjoys wildlife.  When I visited years ago in November flocks of thousands of snow geese would impress anyone.

Beautiful! Peaceful! We were too early in the season to watch migratory fowl but we did see some geese and ducks nonetheless.  Ruts on the wildlife drive but we saw that BH is getting ready to mitigate that situation. Should be absolutely gorgeous in a couple of weeks.

A great place to see native and migratory bird species. Herons, egrets, goldfinch, indigo bunting, geese, terns, and even a red fox makes the rounds and poses for pics. Yes, during summer there are lots of biting flies but around August they start to die down. We wear long sleeves and a hat to step out of the car and snap photos. Very friendly people here that are usually happy to discuss birding and sharing photos.
This place is a Delaware treasure. Great education center and beautiful trails for walking and observing nature in every season.

What a diverse and beautiful natural place untouched pretty much invasives.Giant Highland Blueberry bushes , Exspansive Clethra stands etc etc...tons of migratory water birds and beavers , yes beavers

name: Tidbury Park
address: Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Nice and quiet. My four legged baby enjoys his walks on the little trails. The only downside...is all the mosquitoes . Other than that it's The place to take your four legged babies.
Beautiful park even in a winter!
Lots of bugs. But hey its summer time comes with the territory. Play ground is alright.
Too buggy. The bugs will eat you alive. I won't bring any dogs to this park, We got bugs bite. It good this park is hidden. The trail and water is pretty.
Great place to take your dogs to play and explore. Nice walking/jogging paths.

name: Delaware Public Archives
address: 121 M.L.K. Jr Blvd N, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Look like they have a big close room that you can research but you have to ask a worker to open it for you. They do have a small exhibit and it was WW2 when I went there
This is a must see!
One of the best repositories to do research. The staff is kind and helpful. It's easily accessible by DART 301, if traveling from Wilmington.
I have been very happy with the help that the Delaware Public Archives has provided on several occasions.
Everyone is very friendly and willing to help when  problems occur.  I wish I  would have investigated my family history sooner.  Thank you.

name: Dover Park
address: 1210 White Oak Rd, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Such a shame what a few people who either  have a lack of empathy for others or apathetic in general, did to this place.

Very nice park. 

Disc golf course is very short but there are some challenging lanes you must hit. Definitely fun for a quick game of you are passing through
Hidden gem! the basketball and tennis courts are great.
Beautiful and quaint place to walk
Best place to walk my dog peacefully.

name: 3 Palms Zoo & Education Center
address: 1060 Vandyke Greenspring Rd, Townsend, DE 19734, USA
reviews:
More relaxed experience offering a closer look at the animals. Nice place with helpful friendly staff.
Fun day trip for children & adults.

This was our first time visiting the zoo since they relocated.  The layout is incredibly easy to navigate. The workers there were amazing.  They informed us before they fed the pelicans and took a tortoise out of its enclosure so my 5 year-old and I could watch and pet it.  I also learned so much from Dan about the animals.
When my daughter asked to pet one of the snakes, the gentleman stopped what he was doing to go and get a snake for her.  It was a great time and we are already talking about going back.

It may have changed in the past two years, but when we went there it was dumpy. Their parking area had a srterp drop off so when I pulled out of the lot slowly it tore up the front end of my vehicle. I like people rescuing animals, but the place was advertised as being well kept and at the time of our visit it was not. We had driven about an hour and a half and it was not worth it.

Very clean and nice place to walk around and spend a couple hours. They have plenty of animals and reptiles to see. Employees are very helpful, nice, and knowledgeable. I will glady come back to visit again!
Wonderfully inexpensive place to bring your family!  Great alternative to a traditional zoo

name: Killens Pond Water Park
address: 5025 Killens Pond Rd, Felton, DE 19943, USA
reviews: Reasonable priced so much cheaper than other water parks. They have umbrellas and lounges  to lay in under tarp- it was hot that day water was nice. What's nice too you can bring in your own cooler. It turned out to be a great day !

My kids and I love this park.  There are great slides, the kids love the lily pad walk, toddler pool with mini slides... It's great.  The entry fee is minimal, as of today, $10 for parents, $8 for kids.  I do wish the bathrooms/showers were a little cleaner, or they had some dry stalls just for changing.  The lifeguards pay attention, and they are great as well.  Excellent, cost efficient way to beat the heat and have a blast with your family!  I will have to add pics later.
Wonderful place for big family gatherings, pinics, BBQ's or just a quick get away
Small but very good  water park ......

Four very different water slides. Green and yellow slides are so steep and fast that they make you feel like you are on a roller coaster. Blue is nice for beginners and orange seems to be the most popular. Great kids area and places to swim or just watch too! Loved it!

name: Dover Downs Hotel & Casino
address: 1131 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Lost some money but still fun.
Great casino to go to
Has a good time mom enjoyed herself

I am really impressed by Dover Downs Casino. The casino is clean and stylish, with a Las Vegas feel. Security is present but not in your face, so I feel safe but not intimidated. There are plenty of slots in good working order, not like some casinos​. I definitely will be returning soon.
Love this place!! Great food! Dancing, bars, night life, gambling!! Poker room is awesome, great tournaments, awesome selection of slot machine as well!!

name: DE Turf Sports Complex
address: 4000 Bay Rd, Milford, DE 19963, USA
reviews: Paid parking?  Us parents pay enough for club fees, uniforms, trainers, hotels, fuel, tolls...now parking too?  There are better ways to bring in revenue other than this.  Besides, the complex is in the middle of nowhere with no real amenities around.  Should have been built much further North.  Yes nice fields, but paid parking?  Come on.
Easy access, convenient parking if you us Parkmobile App, excellent playing field, signage could be better...to locate different playing fields.

This is a really nice, new turf complex with some essential amenities (bathrooms and snack bars), but there's not a whole lot else around it, and when all fields are in use, parking can be limited. On top of that, there's a parking fee ($10 per day plus a $0.50 convenience fee). I've never before had to pay a parking fee for a youth soccer event. It doesn't exactly dispel the notion that youth sports are all about making money.

Top Notch facility. I have been to lots of places for tournaments and this is the best so far. 12 turf fields with plenty of grassy areas nearby each field for team warmups and teams to set up tents. Wide sidewalks connect access to all fields and parking was fairly easy. Multiple concession stands throughout with restrooms and working water fountains at each one. There are also plenty of trees planted around sidewalk and  end fields to provide shade. There is also a picnic sheltering the center area. Any other turf filled facilities should come here to see how it should be done.
This has been the best tournament venue I have ever experienced!

name: DuPont Nature Center
address: 2992 Lighthouse Rd, Milford, DE 19963, USA
reviews: What an amazing place! So much wildlife! The guide gave us lots of really helpful information. She said the best time to see horseshoe crabs was in May so we will definitely be going back to find out! Never tire of Delaware! Anyone willing to loan me a house so I can live there?

A nice place to visit.  Well off the beaten path.  If your able to the beach you can see many Horseshoe Crabs.  If they are turned over on their back and still alive turn them over and set them free...

A little out of the way, but a nice place. Small building, but the space is used well and the staff was kind and very knowledgable. Had a great conversation with them. I wish their website had more information regarding events and such. Overall, a nice experience for our kids.

Absolutely stunning, informative, beautiful, and good for all ages and handicapped accessible. And .... FREE! While I was there many bird-watchers with expensive long-lensed cameras invited me to have a look. Inside the science center there was many live creatures to see and learn about. A must see
Great place to go watch osprey, eagles, shore birds, or any other bird that may be local or migrating.

name: Mispillion River Brewing
address: 255 Mullett Run St, Milford, DE 19963, USA
reviews: Phenomenal local bar and creative brews all the time. Nice interior and love the Trivia nights on Mondays. Always recommending this place to friends

Stopped by on a Sunday afternoon on my way back from a road trip with my kids as I was checking Google Maps for breweries in the area. The atmosphere was welcoming and there's a lot to look at in their small taproom. The kids had fun playing the Wii they have hooked up, while I did a few flights to sample the creativity. They had a handful of IPAs on tap. Pineapple Express was great. Try War Llama if they have it on tap. This was a sweet sour beer with a light green hue.
What a GREAT selection of Fantastic  beers, Great atmosphere.

Was looking for somewhere to stop on the way from Ocean City MD to NJ and decided to stop here after visiting Dogfish. Atmosphere was great, and the employees were very helpful. The beer was awesome, and they even had cold brew coffee, which was also very good. Will definitely stop back any time I'm in the area.

Great brewery with great beer for every pallet . Good to find one that isn't 90% IPA based. Tammy was great and my girlfriend and I could have stood there for another hour chatting. 

Never was a fan of sour ales but couldn't help but to get a 4 pack of their War Llama. So good!

name: Frightland
address: 309 Port Penn Rd, Middletown, DE 19709, USA
reviews: Frightland is truly an incredible experience. I've been to many haunted attractions on the east coast, and I can say that Frightland ranks as one of the highest in terms of quality, quantity, and value. The set designs are amazing. The actors are engaging. The scares are genuinely TERRIFYING and top-notch. They have some of the most creative and unique hayride sets that I have ever encountered... I could go on. It's been a long time since a haunt made me jump so much! In comparison to other haunts in the area, Frightland gives you the most for your money with 8 full attractions as well as a full carnival midway (and rides are included with your ticket purchase). The lines do get long at Frightland (because they try their absolute best the make sure that you don't run into the group in front of you). This makes the experience much more enjoyable and personal (as well as much scarier!). You may have to wait a while, but I guarantee you the experience is well worth it! Frightland will be on my list every Halloween season from now on!
An absolute place that you must visit! 😀 Frightland is easily a traditional and favorite place to visit every year.
Great actors! Good scares! Lacks a little in ambiance.

I’ve been to Frightland 3 years in a row about to be 4 and it never fails to disappoint 😁 all the low reviews about the staff being mean and rude, never happened when I was there all 3 years. The website tells you everything you need to know about going, so don’t say that it doesn’t. It’s always gonna be mainly jump scares, there’s not really any other way to terrify people lol. Plus they change something or add something every single year so one bad year shouldn’t stop you from coming. They made the hayride longer and added new Ghouls. I highly recommend this place. Every time I’ve gone, the food has been good. And people are going to cut in line, you’re just gonna have to suck it up. If you want to make it to all the attractions, start with the hayride and you will be fine. I highly recommend starting with the hayride. The first year I didn’t and didn’t make it to all of them. The two years after that, I started with the hayride and made it to all attractions both times. Most of the money goes to a good cause so you’re not wasting it.  Go. To. Frightland!

Had an awesome time here tonight! The hayride was a little disappointing in the beginning, but every other attraction killed it! You will not regret spending those $40, go for it and definitely do all 8 attractions, best bang for the buck.

name: Harrington Raceway & Casino
address: 18500 S Dupont Hwy, Harrington, DE 19952, USA
reviews: First time of going but compared to Dover Downs Casinos I can say that Harrington Casino the payout is higher but they offer very little comp money or really cool free stuff based on the points you have accumulated from playing the slots during that month. They also don't offer much free play. When you play the slots in Dover they offer free slot play once you have accumulated some points and they also offer 25.00 in free slot play when you join to be used the very first day only and then ever few months they may offer anywhere from 15.00 to 50.00 in free slot play. You also get either 2 free night stay for 2 at the casino hotel or percentage off at their spa. So to me even though Harrington pays out more you get more bang for your buck and more incentives at Dover Downs casino and raceway.

Love the casino. Lots of perks if your spending lots of money.  I very rarely win the big bucks. But maybe you will if your willing to spend the big bucks.  Friday's its busy.  There's a band playing in the club if your only interested in great music.  Upstairs is sports being and poker. I play poker and I'm there for hours ago they provide comfortable seats in there as well as in the shorts being area.  The food is great as well all you can eat in certain area's of the casino.
Good place to go have fun a lot more open than other casinos nice outdoor space

The casino was great and the food at Onion Jacks was also great but the service was horrible.  After the Waitress / Bartender brought us our food that was the last we saw of her, never had our drinks refilled and after waiting a while we had to go ask her for our check.  It seems like she was more interested in chatting it up with the bar customers!  We were there tonight 02/19/2020 a she was the blonde waitress.  If she waits on us the next time we are in there we will get up and leave!
Small but just enough of everything you are looking for to enjoy your day. The fair right outside was an Awesome add on

name: Harvest Ridge Winery
address: 447 Westville Rd, Marydel, DE 19964, USA
reviews: All the staff were super friendly.  They have something for everyone's palate.  You can have a seriously dry wine, a syrupy sweet wine, a dessert wine, fruity wine, Sangria,etc.  They have also offer a nice selection of hard ciders.  You can order a pitcher or fill your growler.  You can do a flight or a tasting or just sit and drink a bottle of wine.  It is a fun place.
I love visiting this winery. Their wine is so good!  My favorite is Blue Hen.  They have great events, pairings/tastings and atmosphere for a fun girl’s night 😝

HRW is a gem! The staff is friendly, the space is beautiful, the drinks are great and the events are amazing! There is always something going on. Don't miss out on the Food Truck Fest, doormat workshops and food pairings (just some of the few events offered)!

I came here for the first time a few weeks ago to attend a birthday party. I was very impressed with the property and the whole process of how they welcome guests and present their wine. Wine is also very good and I bought myself some bottles that I continue to enjoy.
Very nice and relaxed place. Friendly and comfortable. Highly enjoyable wines and ciders.

name: Cape Henlopen State Park
address: 15099 Cape Henlopen Dr, Lewes, DE 19958, USA
reviews:
I have been to this park every year since I moved to Delaware.  This years experience was the worst mainly due to the bathrooms and shower house.  They were completely disgusting!  Not only were they nasty...they were just plain unsanitary.  There are 100 plus people using these everyday and they weren't even cleaned once that I could tell.  There was a wait for my wife and daughter to use the bathhouse every time.  They really need to build new larger and more sanitary facilities.  I found it ironic that a sign out side the bathhouse said to pick up after your pets because it's unsanitary.  How about cleaning the bathrooms!  Geez, for $35 a night I think the hosts could do a better job and making sure they were at least hosed out.  

Another reason I disliked this trip was because the WWII tower was closed/locked with no explanation all weekend???  That is one of the reasons I like to go there.  Bike trails are nice.  Beach is very crowed and the only place to go with a dog is to the truck beaches and we almost got run over by trucks on the way out!  C'mon Delaware authorities.  98% of the people on the truck beaches are not fishing!  They are partying!  I think it should be a little more enforced as to the regulations for preservation of the beaches.  JMHO.
My favorite beach in this area!
Beautiful park, tucked on top of Rehoboth Beach. Always lovely. Worth an hour, or a day, or more!
Clean bathhouse at the campgrounds.
Fantastic the day couldn't get better.  Weather, people, the ocean the walking trails even with a cane was great.  Was even able to see New Jersey from the beach.  A Blessed day

name: Lums Pond State Park
address: 1068 Howell School Rd, Bear, DE 19701, USA
reviews: I adore this park. It has great trails and there is much to do here. If you love the great outdoors, this is the place to be. However, I am a bit concerned about the length of hunting season. I wish it was a total safe haven for animals and I feel like some of the deer stands are too close to the camping area.

Spent the weekend, beautiful little campgrounds. The sites are well planned,  a firepit and picnic tables,  full hook up. The playground is awesome,  with mommy and me swings, jungle gym and a really cool nature interactive board with a scope to spot animals. There is a huge field to play in in the middle which is great, keeps kids safe and away from traffic. Bathrooms are clean well lit and the handicapped bathroom is excellently designed! Showers are separate from bathrooms, Yea! There is a laundry with a sink. Several trails surround and spin off the campground. The lake is peaceful with a pier. Very laid back place,  great for couples or families with youngsters!

We love Lums Pond! We stay here every winter. The park has been upgraded over the past couple of years so that all sites are full hookup. This year they have added a small laundry facility that is located right next to the large playground. We will be back!
It’s amazing that such a small state like Delaware has such great state parks. So jump on your gravel bikes and explore the trails of this park. You won’t be disappointed.

We came here to swing through the trees and we did just that. We were here a year or two ago and did the basic ropes course through the trees. Then we came again recently to visit this time we did the advanced course. It was totally worth it and a lot of fun.

name: Constitution Park
address: 301 S State St, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews:
Location: North and State Street, Dover, DE 19901
There is a sculpture in the park. The sculpture and park honors the ratification of the Constitution of the United States.  
The sculpture consists of a 13 foot bronze quill feather laid across a stainless steel cube.
yyyyyyyyeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeetttttttt

name: Abbott's Mill Nature Center of Delaware Nature Society
address: 15411 Abbotts Pond Rd, Milford, DE 19963, USA
reviews: Very nice trails and nature area.  Great for children and school trips!
I enjoyed the tour in the mill.
No one on the trails at sunrise, Beautiful ❤️
In love with creeks glad the trail goes along it
A great nature center to take kids on a quick day trip.

name: Prime Hook National Wildlife Refuge Admin Building And Visitor Contact Station
address: 11978 Turkle Pond Rd, Milton, DE 19968, USA
reviews: I was told 4,000 snow geese flock there. I did not see any. In fact, I saw almost no birds. The area is too vast to explore by foot or car. Boat is probably the better option in warmer weather. Very peaceful though.

I will return to hike the trails and to visit Fowler Beach. Mom and I visited the well equipped Ranger Station and got maps and info.
This NWR was unknown to me and obviously a well-kept secret gem! We spent a lot of time driving the winding roads and on Route 1 that is the only way to reach the winding beach access roads. Protecting the acres of protected bay dunes and marshlands is obviously an important priority. So expect to park and walk to area close to waterways! The dunes are unharmed and I saw a snowy egret and some turtles and visitors crabbing off a bridge over a stream.
I watch, study and maybe photograph Nature and wildlife! Though, this refuge is a resource for permitted hunters of waterfowl in season. I saw info and tags near the eastern entrance. 
I also noticed a trail head for The National Trail System Florida to Canada. Pack lunch this refuge is purely natural. No pizza or fries!
The visitor center was really nice and the man at the counter was amazingly kind and very knowledgeable. Can't wait to come back!!!

great place for birds, bugs, and vistas. I loved learning about all the species of animals and plants by doing the junior refuge manager program. Similar to the junior ranger program with the national park service but different style badge.

We walked the boardwalk path and the other lookout path (which is a little longer and joins with the boardwalk) with a toddler in an umbrella stroller. These paths were very well maintained, but it probably wouldn't be the best idea in muddy weather. The lady at the visitor center was extremely kind and pulled out all sorts of things for our little guy to look at. That said, even with the (very lovely) walks, we were only there a little more than an hour, and older kids would probably be bored, as they don't have very new or unusual displays. If you're looking for nature walks, it is a great choice though.

name: Go Ape Zipline & Adventure Park
address: 1042 Howell School Rd, Bear, DE 19701, USA
reviews: Beautiful place! Just recently started coming back here since I was much younger. Used to always come here with my family as a child so I guess we're starting the tradition back up lol. $8 parking for out of state isn't bad. Boat rentals are fairly cheap compared to other state parks I've been to. Can't wait to stay at their camp site!

Excellent!!!!!! Although some sections scared the POO OUT OF ME!!!!!!😂😂😂😂😂 I chose this for my 12 year old daughter's birthday present and I WAS THE ONE SCARED TO DEATH!!! My gf, my ex-wife, and my 2 daughters had more kahunas than I did!!!!!!! I finished the course though. You will definitely need upper body and core strength to complete the Tree Top Adventure. They also offer another one that's a little less harrowing. Great time had by all and an excellent choice for a fun outing!!!!! This place is inside of a state park. There are grills, picnic areas, and cabanas. The state park is huge, so if you get there early enough (the Tree Top Adventure takes 2-3 hours) there's plenty to do in the state park. Trust me, my pictures do not do this experience any justice!!!
Must visit place for kids . Tree top is short duration but it's worth

I loved the experience even though I had a very hard time going through the course. I must gain strength and lose weight if I ever think about doing this adventure again. Lol Thanks for the push staff.

My husband and I bought five tickets a piece and decided to use it weekly to get ourselves doing some physical activity that wasn't too hard. So we bought the five tickets for the junior course! Today was our first day using it and we had a great time! We are looking forward to the next four weeks and the fun that we will have doing this junior course. We felt very safe. They are very safety conscious and check everything every day!

name: Fort Delaware State Park
address: 45 Clinton St, Delaware City, DE 19706, USA
reviews:
Overall, great experience!  It's started out a little rough when the ferry left early; however, the staff handled the situation perfectly.  The ferry ride was great and definitely added to the experience.  On the island, we paid $5 extra per person for the inside tour, which lasted about 2 and 1/2 hours.  The guide was excellent and very knowledgeable.  Also, we got to see parts of the fort that aren't included in the regular admission.  One important thing to note is that this is a "leave it as is" site; therefore, any trash must taken with you when you leave the island and food and drink options on the island are very limited.

Highly recommended!

I went to the POW event weekend & they have a lot of civil war reenactors. One part of the fort is for only bat tours. The rest of the fort you can walk around & you can use the stairs to get on the top. You can see the bay from the top. The fort do have cannons. There is picnic tables but you will have to take the trash with you. We paid $24 for the ferry for 2 people to go to the island. The ferry ride is around 10min from & to the island.

Great day out, and in beautiful weather.  We had a minor issue with the ferry breaking down, but the delay was minimal, and all staff were great.  The fort and surrounding park area was a beautiful and interesting place.
We've lived here for 35 years.  This was our first trip to this park.  There are boats that take you to the prison.  You need to buy tickets.  There was a great ice cream place across the street.

Great place to take the kids for a day! Had fun looking for ghost, like on Ghost Hunters. Hiked the nature trail biting flies,but a good walk! Kids learned a lot about the history! Been coming here since the1970's before they had electricity in a lot of the areas! Had several scouting events here, everyone seemed to have a good time! And more of the fort was opened to public than now, but still a very good place to come back to! Hard to believe that if you live in, Delaware mainly in New Castle region, and you have not been there to the island you really need to go! And not to forget the boat ride experience! Can't wait to get back there!

name: Bowers Beach Maritime Museum
address: 3357 Main St, Frederica, DE 19946, USA
reviews: Great Museum to visit.  The town is lovely and they have a great benefit event called the 'Bowers Beach Buccaneer Bash' every Memorial Day weekend which is worth checking out to support the Museum. Its a lot of fun and the Museum itself with or without the festival is a grand place to visit.
Very interesting history of the fishing community of Bowers Beach Delaware.
Great place to learn local history!
Wonderful beach community
Neat little place

name: Lewes Beach
address: 206 Bay Ave, Lewes, DE 19958, USA
reviews: Its a good beach, but it can be crowded, especially because of it's location and that it's free to go to. But, other than that, it's a good place to sit by the beach. I recommend this beach to families with their little kids, because the waves won't knock them down if they want to swim in the water.
Enjoyed Dairy Queen while watching the Cape May Ferry come and go, perfect.  Also enjoyed watching the birds. Early March has a lot less people and no paying for parking.

Clean and quiet during the off season
But wait a couple months. Love this quaint little town.
Amazing beach. Lots of parking. Clean. Public restrooms. Went in the off season. Can't say how it is in peak season though.
Great in the off season to stroll with your dog. It's one of my favorite spots to just exhale over a coffee and enjoy the down time out of the high season.

name: New Castle Battery Park
address: 1 Delaware St, New Castle, DE 19720, USA
reviews:
Battery Park is interesting. It really shouldn't be called 'Battery Park' - It should be called the 'Historical Relics Park'! You can Google it's historical significance. However, more interestingly, it still retains remnants of an old pier that used to go into the water. This place still has it's lampposts standing. Walking around here makes for an eerie experience and you can totally take amazing post-apocalyptic photos! It's just a hop away from the nearby historic district. So make sure to go here while you're in New Castle to view some history. 

Recommended!
It was very nice. Park itself was very clean with no trash lying around. However, few area's where there were mounds of geese droppings. So just pay attn where you walk, but all and all very nice!!

Good place for an evening stroll in a culture rich part of Delaware. There are good photo spots and walking trails and even some sandy areas for a beach feel. Recommend this place for casual evening walks, small family picnics and so on.

I grew up 40 years ago in this park. It has been  upgraded and discovered by thousands in part because of the pokemon go. Now during the summer hundreds enjoy the park every day. It has a waterfront walking path kids climbing entertainment area with slides. It has a dwarf, but you cannot fish. It has a sailing club. Great small town park.
Nice place for pics. Interesting, historical looking town. We went at night so I hope to enjoy it in the day when it's bright and warmer.

name: Pizzadili Vineyard & Winery
address: 1683 Peach Basket Rd, Felton, DE 19943, USA
reviews: I liked Pizzadili. The woman there was very knowledgeable about the wines, and the wines were a fascinating old-fashioned exploration both of terrior and older, traditional Italian-style winemaking techniques. I was really facinated by the white wines that spent contact on the skins; loved both the Deleware and the Niagara.  My favorite of the reds was the Two Brothers Chambourcin and Cab blend. Recorded a podcast for my blog about the Delaware a few nights ago, actually, as that was the bottle that came back with me.

We love to stop in here a couple of times a year to try out their new wines. With the Pizzadili's, wine-making is an art they brought with them from Italy. They love what they do, and they make some very good wines. They have a great little gift shop there as well, so if you know a wine lover, this is the place to buy them a birthday present. Do a tasting and they will be happy to tell you about each wine. I love it that they all are so down to earth and willing to share what they know about their craft.

Ignore most of the negative reviews. Some of the neighbors are upset because Pizzadili was opposed to allowing a dirt track raceway to be built next to their business.
Great wine selections, nice friendly people and beautiful grounds.
Good staff and tasting. Had limited time, but Bought a case.
Excellent wines. knowlodgeable staff.

name: First State Heritage Park Welcome Center and Galleries
address: 121 M.L.K. Jr Blvd N, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: This is a great constellation of living history museums the state archives and legislature. Tours are easy to set up for your class group; and if you want to visit there is no fee for parking or admittance. Lots of great portraiture of Delaware notables throughout our history.
Nice building, good selection of brochures available. I think the front desk attendants were surprised to have visitors. The restrooms were clean and convenient.
Nice place for information.
Me encanta! Todo de esta bella ciudad me encanta,  visiten Dover y sus alrededores, vale la pena conocer

name: Fort Miles Historical Area
address: 15099 Cape Henlopen Dr, Lewes, DE 19958, USA
reviews: Be sure to take the tour of the bunker! The tour was amazing

My kids and I love this place.  It’s a nice “add-on” experience to a day at the beach at Cape Henlopen State Park.  We do a monthly day-trip throughout the summer and early Fall.  They have one observation tower that you can climb, several historic WWII canons and anti-aircraft guns, barracks and a bunker that they have restored.  The bunker is a nice option when it’s really hot out because it’s underground and cool.  Amazing photos and artifacts inside the bunker.
The view is beautiful and Fantastic, beside you can ride a bicycle to see all the guns with your children on outdoor with the parking lot at low fee.

This place is an amazing piece of history. They have some really interesting artillery and it is a great place for kids to learn to learn. My son got to stand in the barracks where his great grandfather slept before shipping off to Italy as an MP. I'm incredibly grateful that it has been preserved and that I was able to share the experience with my family!
Very interesting history and quite a few guns. Makes a nice walk on a nice day.

name: Midway Speedway Park
address: 18645 Coastal Hwy, Rehoboth Beach, DE 19971, USA
reviews: My grandchildren had a great time on the bumper boats and then on Fire Mountain Mini Golf. It made for an AWESOME  afternoon of fun with Mom-mom.  We always enjoy Midway and we come back every year at least a few times. Next time its GO KARTS...  YEAH....
Awesome my two little ones and my husband have MUCH Fun and I watching them 😍.The staff  makes us feel so pleasant while we were there !
Always a fun place to take the family and good prices
The guys had a awesome back to childhood fun! The girls shared laughs! Awesome staff!
Awesome park! We had so much fun here. At the end if you win the last hole, you win a free game.

name: Longwood Gardens
address: 1001 Longwood Rd, Kennett Square, PA 19348, USA
reviews: GORGEOUS. Flowers are SPECTACULAR. A must see. Best to visit often, at least once for every season. I love the STUNNING ORCHIDS IN BLOOM as much as their CHRISTMAS DISPLAY. Can't wait to return in the summer to see the fountains & outdoor gardens in Bloom. Will be wearing COMFORTABLE SHOES! Food was LOVELY, a little overpriced, but DELICIOUS. Its a BEAUTIFUL place to visit.

This place is an experience.  Full of rich history and breathtaking scenery.  The grounds are kept pristine and beautiful.  Do yourself a favor and give yourself at least two days here because there is that much to see.  I've been twice so far, once in the summer and once at Christmas time and both times were unique.  If you can, see the fountain shows and see the Christmas displays for sure.  You won't be disappointed.

One of my favorite places to be. Always something new to see on each trip. Great to go to some of my favorite spots in the gardens & see how it looks different with each season.

Wonderful place to get away and just relax. Some days it’s hiking in the meadow on the trails. Other days it might be sitting on a bench & watching the fountains or waterfalls.

Definitely worth a membership & the hour drive.

Simply the best! Go at Christmas, it's a magical escape and it will put you into the holiday spirit. We went on a drizzly night with lots of mist in the air which created an ethereal setting, the outdoor lights diffused and eerie. Loved it! The gigantic greenhouse goes on and on and on; there was a huge pipe organ and an organist and at least 75 people participating in A Christmas carol sing along which was delightful. Everybody was singing! It was really nice that all those strangers were coming together in that moment. Make sure you look for the unique and somewhat odd bathroom area with little pods that run along a curved hallway. The hall walls have plants growing up them. Our friends showed us this and it was a lot of fun to visit the round restrooms! Hit up the on-sight restaurant; one of the best meals we've had this past year. Just outside the restaurant there was a bar area with good micro brews. Lots of fun on a Friday evening with minimal crowds. I think the rain helped us out.

We went here during the orchid extravaganza in March. Had a wonderful time. The diversity of scenery (even in the winter months) is extraordinary. Meadows, forests, topiary, fountains, treehouses and greenhouses that are filled to capacity with flowers. Beautiful places to walk. Some areas paved, others are not. Definitely bring good walking shoes.

Their main exhibit at the time were the orchids in the conservatory. Beautiful arrangements of orchids on walls and hanging baskets, along with bonsai trees, succulents, and hybrid orchid varieties. They definitely put a lot of care into their exhibit to make sure it is well maintained.

Price-wise, the entrance tickets are a little expensive at $25 dollars a person. The prices at the cafe inside are also steep. Because of this though, the gardens, buildings, and fountains are very well maintained. And the food is decent quality. They definitely put the money to good use creating and maintaining the beautiful landscape.

If your in the Philadelphia area and looking for a fun day trip, definitely check out Longwood Gardens.

name: First State National Historical Park
address: 211 Delaware St, New Castle, DE 19720, USA
reviews:
If you are looking for national park Cancellation Stamps you will find one at the first State visitor center. Or if like history this little square will work you away to colonial times.. parking on the weekend in Sept was easy and close. They have a little 8 min movie and some local artifacts including a little walking tour of the area.
#AdventureKrewe tip: take a photo of the walking tour sign and use it to navigate the streets, then use Google to look up each location. Your own mini history tour.
Give us things up if you like American history. Two thumbs up if you don't.

Beautiful place in the First State. A great place to visit any time but especially when they have events.  Check their website for events.  Also a good place for children, plenty of space to run around and a nice playground.
Great place. Awesome accesible waterfront close to historic New Castle. Cafés and Restaurants nearby. Minimal trash along the shore and runner and dog friendly trails.
Neat little place. Not exactly what I had expected but very history filled area
This is the only national park site in Delaware.  The building and streets are beautiful! The people are nice and friendly. They give you so much ibformation!!

name: Jungle Jim's
address: 36944 Country Club Rd, Rehoboth Beach, DE 19971, USA
reviews: A pretty good water park near the beach. Wasn't too crowded but it was Thursday. Had 2 fun slides. 4 slower quick slides. But no lines. Lazy river was fun to just chill. No alcohol. Food at cafe wasn't too bad as far as price. Flavor wasn't bad either. Price overall was a bit high but to be expected.
Great place for the family. Very clean as well

Nice place to come and relax, slides are an extra fun for adult and kids. Plenty to do for toddler's as well.  The anaconda slide is especially fun due to the slide resembling that of a snake.  Food here is at a pretty reasonable price. Plenty of life guards changing up almost ever 30 mins to an hour.

at first you kind of taken back by the price +$100 for a family of 3. Parking is free, and once inside your greeted with a clean crowd free activity environment.

There are water attractions for all ages and interest.

This is definitely a place we will visit again.

I had a blast here, and so did the kids. Perfect size for a water park. Not too crowded,  easy to get around, areas for young kids to play (splash pads).

The food area was good as well, your typical staples, pizza, chicken tenders, fries, hot dogs. 

The bumper boats were a blast. You get to pilot a small boat, and as the name would suggest bump into other floating contraptions with sentient beings inside (read: boats with people).

The lazy river was awesome. We probably went around 10 times by the end. 

Highly recommend a trip here. Much more fun than sesame place in all honesty.

name: White Clay Creek State Park
address: Park Office, 750 Thompson Station Rd, Newark, DE 19711, USA
reviews: Nice park though the mapping is inconsistent with actual trail conditions.. many trails shown on maps are now simply closed or no longer on the trails as indicated.. trail markers encountered are not all updated w/new trail info or accurate.. I had 3 maps and honestly none were correct.... the DE access lots are only  free  from December 1st  to March 1st.. there is very little here worth an $8 per vehicle out of state parking charge so be warned..  use the adjunct Pa lots to avoid these ridiculously high user fees.. no state park w/o lifeguarded swimming available should be more than $3 for anyone to day use ..
Such a beautiful place. We ran a cross country meet here. Awesome course.

We enjoyed the short hike by the rangers station. The GPS got me there with no problem. I'm going to purchase a yearly pass so I can explore as much as I can of the park.
My. Man

Nice big park. Took a 6 mile walk and didn't cover all the trails. Their are some good hills to get your heart rate up. Clean restrooms and very nice picnic shelters. Great place for a hike or family outing.
Perfect place for hikes and bike rides, either alone or in groups. Wonderful scenery and trails.

name: Zwaanendael Museum
address: 102 Kings Hwy, Lewes, DE 19958, USA
reviews: The Zwaanendael Museum is a great little Museum filled with amazing history and artifacts from the Town and surrounding areas. The stall and Volunteers were very friendly and very informed about the area and its history. They relayed their love for the area and their bountiful knowledge to us in a easy and fun way.

This place is neat. First,  it's easy to find and Lewes is a pretty town.  The museum is free and contains items from a shipwreck along with interesting information. There is an art display upstairs. If you have any Dutch heritage this would be good to visit. Nice restaurants within walking distance.
We visited to see the merman. The museum itself is lovely as well as the outside grounds. Staff were curious and knowledgeable.

Interesting museum. It's tiny, two floors, so you won't be there all day. Info video on the main level is worth watching since it tells you all the stuff you should know about Lewes. Some nice art work. Staff there is are very friendly and informative. It's free.

This museum/park is truly unique. I didn't go in the museum because I have my 2 little dogs with me. I learned a lot from the signs outside. The park is small and clean, and well equipped with a fully functional restroom, trash cans, doggy poop stations.

name: Delaware Children's Museum
address: 550 Justison St, Wilmington, DE 19801, USA
reviews:
We had a 2nd birthday there. It was AMAZING. Olivia, our party leader was wonderful with the kids and with helping me get everything ready. All the guests had a blast and we even got vouchers for the kids we paid for that couldn't make it. 

The museum itself was great. Really clean. And the exhibits had something for all kids ages. Even the parents had fun playing. I seriously can't recommend this place enough.

Cannot say enough about how wonderful this place is!! We are members and visit often and our three year old never runs out of things to try! Programs and art activities are well run and simple enough to do even during a quick visit. Staff are super friendly and even when it is crowded they do a fantastic job keeping the place tidy and organized.

Many different rooms, each with it's own theme. Perfect for 4 year olds, with some areas or activities less accessible to younger kids. They have a large water table that my two year old could interact with, although taller, stronger, and older in general makes it a lot more fun. Other kids helped her so it actually worked out beautifully. There are areas meant for younger kids so it depends on what interests your child has and we mainly noticed because we were there with a 3 year old so the accessibility  and interest by age was apparent. My husband and I also enjoyed it since it is set up for learning.

The Delaware Children's Museum was simply delightful! I was worried about what an almost walking 13 month old would be able to do, and the answer is: a lot!

We loved the little kids'area with the trains and the magnetic gears. The mock farmers market was also great, though certainly meant for slightly older toddlers. We didn't venture into any of the areas where the bigger kids were playing.

They have very large family restrooms, for which we were extremely grateful. Diaper changes for a worked up toddler can be a two adult job! 

We were very pleased to see that we could host a birthday party there, and for a very reasonable price. There are a variety of themes designed specifically with the interested and abilities of certain age groups in mind.

Wonderful! My two and a half grandson had a blast. Didn't know where and what to do first. The different areas had appropriate age levels listed and appropriate items for those age groups. It was fun. We'll be back !

name: Carousel Park
address: 3700 Limestone Rd, Wilmington, DE 19808, USA
reviews: Great place to take the kids. They have a large playground and horse stables which you can walk through and pet the horses. It's also a perfect place to take your energetic dog. It's such a large park that most dogs (and owners) would be exhausted if you walked the whole thing.  In the summer we frequent their farmers market where they invite local farmers to bring their vegetables, meats, dairy products, and plants.
Amazing dog park. Huge open field, giant pond for the swimmers. It isn’t completely fenced in but pretty surrounded with woods. People are always extremely friendly and welcoming.
Great dog park! Lots of room for them to run around unleashed. Plus, there's a place for them to take swim to cool off. Highly recommend.
Perfect for picnic. It has a beautiful play area for children. A view of horses, a nice waterbody with goose and a route to ride bike or just hike.

beautiful local park, great walking path through the wooded areas and around the lake. Dog park is great for your dog- leashed or  not. it is a carry in carry out so bring a bag for any trash, there are cans on the way in/out of the park. Friday's there is a Farmers market, the County/State house their horses here and are beautiful to see! Equestrian events, and local track meets.

name: Delaware Outdoor Trail SC875
address: 2658 Cedar St, Lewes, DE 19958, USA
reviews: Wonderful spot to enjoy the tranquility of nature. You can simply sit in your car and take in the view. Listen to the sounds of boats & birds. Or, you can slip off your shoes, take a peaceful stroll along the beach. Feel the sand squishing between your toes, feel the water as it breaks on the beach. The fresh yet calming scent in the air.  **Perfect spot to enjoy with friends, a loved one or even just to be alone.
Great place to do some fishing and relax.

It was a day I needed  to remember. Two dear Young friends I say young because they gave the ultimate sacrifice in Vietnam. Walter was my Church going buddy and Billy was my neighborhood buddy, especially fishing. Thank you American Legion Family of Post 17 of Lewes for having the Moving Memorial Vietnam Veterans Wall this weekend. I thank Billy, Walter& all Veterans for the freedom & liberty they defend so we can enjoy life. Godspeed U.S.A.
Great place for sunset photos and fishing.
Great shoreline location for scenic dawn or dusk photographs.  Popular for fishing in the inlet and beach access to Lewes Beach.

name: Friends-Concord Point Lighthouse
address: 700 Concord St, Havre De Grace, MD 21078, USA
reviews: The town of Havre de Grace is full of rich history with its period home, military science museum home made candy and ice cream shop and most definitely the lighthouse. Whenever I’m returning south from a road trip Havre de Grace is one of my favorite spots. I enjoy photography the bridge from the dock as well as sitting on a bench at the pier and simply enjoy the view of the Potomac. The sunsets are some of the best I’ve experienced in my lifetime. A stop at the welcoming center will give you all the information and history you need to know. Ask about future events. There is always something exciting and fun happening.
Nice quiet place to take a stroll or watch the sunrise. It’s difficult to see the sunset from here, but it’s still nice to go on a full moon night. Very quiet safe area.

Have de grace is a really cozy must stop if you're in the area. Beautiful surroundings and a really nice boardwalk park. Excellent coffee shop, plenty of good quality restaurants, quite a few genuine antique shops and a really great memorabilia and film/music/bookstore that also carries some 1st and 2nd edition  rare and classic books (sometimes also signed by the author).
Really relaxed ambiance and an amazing fourth of July fireworks show every year. Right by the water so a truly great stop anytime of year.
Well maintained, good view. You can get some interesting historical tidbits from the keeper if you press him. The visitors center also has a good little museum and friendly staff.
I enjoyed every moment of it and the light house is so amazing. If you never been here before like myself you have to come see for yourself, something for the whole family. Love, love.

name: Martinak State Park
address: 137 Deep Shore Rd, Denton, MD 21629, USA
reviews: Weekend stay with wife and baby, to start new year off. Stayed in full service cabin. It's really nice and peaceful. The cabin is great. Has 2 pull out sofas in the living room 1 queen and 1 single. The has 2 twin beds in the bedroom. Full kitchen, with full size refrigerator and freezer and stove with oven. The views are great, the river kinda wraps around the front of the cabin and then there is a small pond in the back that you overlook while sitting on the screened in porch. Very nice , we will return. Good Verizon cell service.
It was nice to take the puppy there for a walk...now if we could just train him to walk nicely.

This place is always so clean and absolutely beautiful. Great place for boating, beautiful amphitheater, Sweet Little trails, several really great playground equipment areas, it's a great place to camp and a beautiful place to spend the day.

RV sites are black top and level, very nice park for camping among the trees. Being a state park, you only get power, no water n sewer hookup on site but fresh water supply n dump station is available inside park. Grocery n essentials are right down the street so very convenient if you forgot to bring or need anything. Even though you are so close to main highway, the park is very quiet n you wud not suspect you are so close to town. Love the theater seating pavilion that sits right on the water. Wud be a great place to hold a group event.

Small park but fun for a camping weekend. Only a few short hiking trails but they do have a paved activity trail which seems stroller/wheelchair accessible. Looked like good places for kayaking and they have a nice boat launch. Good fishing spots.

name: Hagley Museum
address: 200 Hagley Creek Rd, Wilmington, DE 19807, USA
reviews: Hagley in and of itself has a nice historic presentation on industry on the Brandywine River.  The docents do a great job with the visitors, especially school-age children. It's a pretty place for a walk along the river, too.  However, the STEM event we lucked into was awesome.  My granddaughters loved the hands on learning, and came away with a lot of enthusiasm to continue doing similar things at home. Fun, but not a Disney princess.  It was great!

We are members but decided to go on one of the coldest days of this winter so far... The place is beautiful, even when there is no green in the trees... The staff are delightful and made the best of it when the welcome center suddenly lost power... On the shuttle up to the house, we saw a bald eagle swooping over the Brandywine River looking for fish and on the way back we saw him perched in a tree. Hagley is well worth a visit in any weather...
Wow! What a gem! We had a blast during our first visit and can't wait to return! So many fun activities for kids plus plenty of historical and technical info for my husband! 😊

This was a great experience. We enjoyed a tour of the family home with a very knowledgeable guide. After which we went down for a demo in the machine shop and then the gun powder demo both of which were educational and entertaining. We ran out of time to see the workers area. It nice that the ticket allows you entrance in 2 days.
A beautiful museum village that brings to life the story of the origins of the DuPont family, Delaware and the Brandywine Valley.  Knowledgeable staff, first rate preservation in a bucolic setting.

name: New Castle Court House Museum
address: 211 Delaware St, New Castle, DE 19720, USA
reviews: Great museum but it's only lead by tour and is not free to roam.

Beautiful and well-preserved building, part of the  First State National Historic Park and promoted as one of its seven main attractions. We walked in and were greeted by a friendly bearded gentleman, who gave us a wonderful 40-minute tour for free. It was through his stories that the place came to life and made us appreciate its historic significance. The tour ended at the second floor, where there is a small exhibition on the history of European settlement in Delaware.

We visited in the summer and the air-conditioned interior was definitely a welcome break from the intense heat. They also have clean restrooms at the basement.
The lady here is very informative, helpful and personable.  It really made the exp experience most enjoyable.
When a 7 year old boy stole a loaf of bread or didn't pay attention to his parents he was taken out to the whipping post and made an those were the good old days literally....
Very knowledgable and personable staff. Cool history.

name: East Point Lighthouse
address: 10 Lighthouse Rd, Heislerville, NJ 08324, USA
reviews: Great Little lighthouse and bay that I've been visiting all of my life. I grew up about 40 minutes away and my dad and I would take evening trips to visit the lighthouse and go to the diner nearby for a slice of pie. This lighthouse will always hold a special place in my heart and I always tell people visiting the area to take the drive and check it out. The Horseshoe crabs that frequent the shore are awesome too!

Despite being off the beaten path, the East Point Lighthouse is well worth the trip! Very picturesque, there were people taking photos for their Christmas card when we were there. It's not very tall so if you're afraid of heights it's not a problem, but it's tall enough to get a great view of the Delaware Bay and Maurice River. The staff is so friendly and informative. There are many items displayed that are from the early to mid 1900s. But the coolest feature is you can actually turn on the light yourself! Ask them how, they'll be happy to tell you. This may/is the only lighthouse you can do this!

Place is scenic, good for stargazing or photography. Staff is friendly and knowledgeable about the history of the site. Place needs help with more donations so be sure to contribute if you can. Fair warning, it's infested with biting flies during certain warm months of the year and they DO NOT give an F about bug spray. Wearing long sleeve and pants and long socks can go a long way to protecting yourself ( cover that neck too). Scarves could be used to cover face as well if they are particularly aggressive. If you are doing photography here this is a must. Heed this warning.

The lighthouse wasn't open when we went but still so much to enjoy. We were able to walk along the water, find shells and rocks. Just had a beautiful day. It wasn't crowded, cars came and left fast. It's just a great place to enjoy nature not so much lay out or swim like on a beach. We just wanted to relax and enjoy the sounds of the water so it was perfect for us. We got to see around the lighthouse just not inside it. We'll go another time to do a lighthouse tour though. We will come back that's for sure.
Nice place to visit.  Historic with knowledgeable and friendly staff

name: Rehoboth Art League
address: 12 Dodds Ln, Rehoboth Beach, DE 19971, USA
reviews: Love to wander in the gardens there. Yearly art festival is a must do .!

Friendly professional atmosphere in the main Gallery, situated on an inspiring peaceful campus!
Dropped off two of my framed  photos ... One for the Members Fine Art Exhibit (Reception this Friday) & one for the great Members Gallery at the Rehoboth Art League. Visit during their posted hours and enjoy an incredible variety of creative expressions in just about all media throughout the year!! Purchase a work of art that will continue to thrill you in your home! Check out their classes for enlightenment and growth, too! Reminder: the Outdoor Show weekends are coming up! Some members are in the SEDAST in Nov. as well (Google it!).

The environment is so peaceful. The idea that local artists can exhibit their work here is comforting. And the art is really outstanding. There are paintings, photographs, clay work, wood, glass, textile... You name it, you can find it there.

The “White Line Woodcut” printmaking class offered by Fred Dylla is a wonderful addition to the RAL’s class offerings.  Fred’s experience in academia, and skill with white line woodcuts shine through in this carefully constructed curriculum.
