Fred’s thoughtful instruction in technique, and historical information about the origins of the “Provincetown Print”, allow students to immediately immerse themselves in this art form.

Fred makes this course easily accessible to artists and non artists alike, with many hands on demonstrations and one on one instruction.  He also has the unique ability to bring a diverse group of strangers together and build them into a supportive group of friends, with activities that enable everyone to get to know their classmates.  Fred proved to the non illustrators in the group that you don’t need special art skills to be able to make lovely prints.  Anyone can learn this!

Fred’s enthusiasm for the subject is so contagious that six months after taking his first workshop, our original group is still meeting weekly to make prints!  Join this workshop the next time around, you will love it.
Great open house event. Lots of local artisans and their crafts.

name: Nassau Valley Vineyards-Winery
address: 32165 Winery Way, Lewes, DE 19958, USA
reviews: Great people. Really good wine.  Sunday marketplace with the music is really nice.

Being close to Rehoboth Beach, I thought this place would be top of the world quality with wines but the tasting room staff just left us wanting. Simple questions about the wines were met with seeming confusion. The person actually just said they know white wine because it's yellowish colored. That says enough right there. There's room for some good competition to come in as this area is a great place for a winery that cares.
Called twice about information on having a wedding there. Both times my name was taken and told I’d be sent information.... never heard back or emailed.
Good wine,  tastings.  Sunday afternoon farmers/craft market  Nice place to visit if in the Rehobeth DE area.

Great wine, though it gets very busy and they are ill prepared for a huge crowd. They definitely make the best of it with their interesting set-up though, but don't expect to step in for a tasting last minute. Get there at least an hour and a half before close to guarantee a spot.

name: Delaware Museum of Natural History
address: 4840 Kennett Pike, Wilmington, DE 19807, USA
reviews: This is a great museum. They have some really cool collections and events for both adults and kids. They also have no problem with this being a out stop when I run along 52. Always a good buzz at this place - love it!

This museum, strictly in terms of the interior, is not ideal. The dinosaur exhibit room contains mostly screens and video game like consoles even during other events it designed for an older more screen based child. The children’s room has a number of hands on activities but after 1-2 visits it loses all appeal and charm because they are the unchanged. The depiction of animals throughout the museum are cold and not engaging for children and adults alike. I know this isn’t the Smithsonian but it could be so much more, especially considering the beauty and location of this building.

So much to see and do.
My grand daughter wants to go every other week.  Very kid friendly and a great staff.
It's small and simple. It's self guided so you can go at your own pace. Lots of things to touch for the kids. Inside and a few things outside. Seems geared towards kids and field trips.
Awesome place! Great for field trips, great for kids and adults both!! Unique exhibits and cool artifact stuff.

name: DuPont Environmental Education Center of Delaware Nature Society
address: 1400 Delmarva Ln, Wilmington, DE 19801, USA
reviews: Discovered this free urban wildlife and nature refuge after walking about 1 mile from the Delaware RiverWalk shopping area. The center exhibits were closed Monday when we visited but the boardwalks and trails were open.  It's reclaimed from an industrial area of the Christina River.
A surprising Oasis at the end of a very pleasant 30 minute stroll by the River. Highly recommendable, in particular the visitor center
Great place to bike and walk. Nature museum is great, bring some binoculars to get a good view of the Beaver Dams.
Very nice walking trail!
I am a frequent visitor to this wonderful boardwalk in the marshes.  There is something new to see everytime

name: Parvin State Park
address: 701 Almond Rd, Pittsgrove Township, NJ 08318, USA
reviews: It's still well kept park. Cabins and lean-too are in excellent shape. As a child my parents and grandparents would rent a cabin at Thanksgiving. We took our dogs AND cats with us to enjoy it. I'll post a Pic after I find my photo album of the bunks. Our cats and dogs are in that Pic. I have fond memories of there. I still rent a cabin now n then. Need to take my daughter to show her and take a nice hike. The trails are phenomenal as, well. I highly recommend this place 💞💞💞
Very clean Park and a great place to be romantic and watch the sunset with your special someone.. Great place to ride bikes and get some quite time
Great trails, fairly easy to walk round. Free parking.  Some great lake views and very clean.

Parvin State Park has been a wonderful place for me for the past 25 years. Fishing, canoeing, swimming. It's kinda dated, but as you can see it's absolutely gorgeous. Check out Ant's kayaks and canoes for rentals; prices were a bit steep but the service was good, and the lake was crystal clear. They had a little a refreshment shack there that covered the basics. Overall, a great family day. Have not done any camping there since it's only 30 minutes from where I grew up.

Went camping here with family in mid-September, and it was a great time to go. Took canoes and paddle boats on the water and there was a lot to explore, tons of wildlife to see and everyone on the water was very nice. There was someone employed by Jersey parks who held a micro-invertabrae exploration session that was very cool for all ages. (Most of) The campsites are large and well spaced out, some lead directly to the boating areas, others lead to picnic areas. IDEAL time, will definitely return. Be on the lookout for the state police, as he verified our non-alcoholic beer bottles one morning.

name: Vincenzo's Pizzeria & Gelato
address: 1035 Forrest Ave, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews:
My wife and I had a delicious lunch few weeks ago in the restaurant. We were greeted and seated in the beautiful renovated dining room  by a very friendly woman. 
We were so happy to see Vinny who is always so lovely and makes you feel at home. Lunch was delicious,the waitress was excellent.
We can’t wait to come back n try the dinner menu.

We started to come here for special occasions and it exceeds our expectations every time! The food, the drinks and the staff are all amazing. They make it worth every dollar, every time. Plus we never leave without leftovers! I recommend this place to everyone

Pizza was pretty good and only slightly pricey. I was disappointed that when we picked up 4 large pizzas they didn't offer any free soda or even plates and napkins for our takeout order. And while it tasted good, it was weird to have a margarita pizza with arugula and stead of basil. The pizzas also could have had slightly more sauce. I didn't want to ask for extra sauce not knowing initially how much sauce normally comes on it. We will try out other pizza places in Dover, but are likely to come back to this one again.

Recommend to everyone. Food was great. 

I have been there a few times and each time it is really good.  The place is very clean and has a comfy seats. The place has a nice are inside and out with nice pictures tables and looks. Then once I got inside it became better. The staff was friendly and helped us to a table then took the order very fast which was nice. The pizza was the best it was the perfect slice and was cheap for what you get. Would recommend to anyone.  The place is very different from before. But I can’t wait to come back many more times.

Ducked in with the sis, Cousin Mike and Karen, and their brats for some outstanding Italian food! 
* Massive Chicken Parm portion
* Best Fettuccine Alfredo I've ever had! Abundant chicken! 
* Excellent Balsamic Vinegar dressing, nom! 
* Bread and Olive Oil with every meal. 

Fairly priced, family vibe and energy, gorgeous looking pizzas! AHHHH!

Cabeza Out!

name: 33 West Ale House & Grill
address: 33 W Loockerman St, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: We were down in Dover to take my mother in law out to dinner for her birthday. My niece, who is local recommended 33 West for something different to try. It doesn't look like much when you first walk in. Very simple. But not in a bad way. They have a good beer menu and the blood orange martini was on point. They have different and interesting menu items. The brussel sprout appetizer is a must! Delicious! Our table had a variety of items from burgers and tacos to my pork belly and fried green tomatoes. Fabulous! If I had a negative it would be slow service. Very friendly though.
Phenomenal time at 33 West. If you're a fan of Dive bars/restaurants and enjoy a great selection of food or beer? This is your place. Not to mention the service is fantastic.
Awesome food! We went last week to Taco Tuesday and the taco's were soooooo good.  Every Tuesday they have a different two taco's. Look forward to seeing what next week has to offer :)

Hit The Mark! Stumbled upon 33 while in Dover overnight on business. Service, atmosphere, quality, & flavor were all just right. Eclectic vibe and diverse crowd on a Tuesday night gave all the right cues we had chosen well. 2 things that drive up the review: 1-With the somewhat open kitchen I noticed the cook changing gloves often, thanks for that. 2-One of the cooks came out to work with another guest on her special order. The Eggplant Stack was full of flavor and cooked just right. Buffalo wings brought just the right heat and a touch of sweet. Other options caught my eye, so I'll have to get back:)

The entrance is uninviting but once your round the corner to the bar area it is a cozy dinner spot. The Shrimp & Spinach was great with the miso ginger dressing. The Pan Seared Tuna Steak was cooked nicely but could have used some seasoning. Overall a good experience.

name: Yukon Korean BBQ & Sushi Bar
address: 865 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews:
I ate spicy ramen and my son ate shrimp udon. They were both great! Definitely we will repeat this place.

I’ve read some other reviews, and noticed some complaint about their service. Oh well, they do not offer 5 star customer service. But they provide enough service, and definitely not rude at all!!!
They are just very shy and quiet voice. 

Well, food taste awesome! We saw lot of customer came in alone. Comfortable and relaxing atmosphere with tasty food.That’s what you can get here!!
The food was wonderful and very fast. The quality was excellent, the service friendly, and the probs very large. I would definitely eat here again!

I love the food here but over the last few years this place has changed. You do not get soup and salad when ordering two rolls anymore. Fish cakes used to come with certain meals but now we must always pay for them. Everything is still the same price (or higher) but you are now getting less. The staff is also noticeably less friendly and welcoming. It’s starting to seem more and more like it’s all about the bottom line and less about customer satisfaction.
Very nice  restaurant. There is a lot of tasty asian food.
Another great evening. Came in a little more than an hour before close with a big party. They accommodated us and we had no issues.

name: Roma Italian Restaurant
address: 3 President Dr, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: We had a fantastic experience.  The food was authentic Italian and everything was delicious from the appetizers through dessert.  We had a large party and the service was impeccable, we never had to wait and the orders came out perfectly.  The only critical feedback, and it's not a show stopper, is the room we were in was loud.  We had a fantastic time and will return.

I was very disappointed.   Unfortunately we had to be in the Dover area during the Valentine's weekend.  Decided to make the best of it and went out to what was described as good and somewhat romantic spot.  
Made a reservation for early evening.  We arrived and our table was waiting.   Table wobbled.   First problem.  Second problem was the interior was ice cold.  My wife had to wear her coat to be warm and comfortable. Third problem was our salmon was served with a mixed vegetable that did not go well with the fish.  My wife requested angle hair pasta in place of mashed potatoes.  When the pasta was served it clearly was not angle hair.
Then we were told that angle hair was not on the menu and that what was taking so long to serve it.  The night was not good and we eventually went somewhere else to eat.
Staff was good, polite and professional.

We went out for a birthday dinner, and everything from the moment we walked in was amazing. Our server Hannah was so kind and attentive, The young gentleman Ty who seated us was so pleasant. The food was absolutely delicious. From the appetizer to the dessert.  We will definitely be coming back.

Amazing food! Nice cozy feeling.  Would recommend for a date night destination.  Only issue we had was the waiter was on top of us asking how every other bite of food was. All in all, very nice place!

Roma Restaurant leaves Vincenzo in the dust. The difference is like night & day!!! All waiters and waitresses were very friendly and helpful. The warm bread and dipping oil was so good.  Dinner was super and I would definitely return not only for dinner but lunch as well!!! Very well run Restaurant, the ambiance is very welcoming and relaxing!

name: Grey Fox Grille and Public House
address: 140 S State St, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Great food! Pleasant atmosphere. The Sous Chef visited our table to see how our meal went. This was a very pleasant surprise. In the several places we've eaten, that has never happened. We will come back for another meal.

Lunch prices are fair but hubby's meatball hoagie was a tad spare. 
I got the Turkey Reuben and it was made perfectly, but again,  a little spare. 

Both tasted good but disappeared too quickly. 

I got the tots and I thought it was something homemade. Seemed like something out of a freezer bag, and came out lukewarm. I mentioned this and was able to get new HOT fries.

The fries are almost too little for finger food and since they come in a stack they present as such.  Dumping them on the plate showed how teeny they were.  I think to be served in a stack or even eaten with a fork, they need more size. Also for more "tooth" satisfaction. 

I am a potato person so the perfect potato side could have made this a 5 star meal, even with the moderate portions. Maybe next time and I believe there will be a next time.

A spectacular spot in downtown Dover for dinner and/or drinks. The only, and I Emphasize only reason I didn't give it 5 stars is that it closes too early! It would be a great place to hang out until midnight or later. The food is great the selection at the bar is great, but it closes too early.

I loved the atmosphere... The music and the quaint little lights on the table... The food was very good. And very nice proportions... Only problem I had was that I couldn't find the food that was on this site. I'm assuming they changed the menu?

This is such a unique amazing place to go they have these really cool interactive murder mysteries  they do to support the local charity Choose Joy and it is so much fun you have got to try it and it is for a good cause .

name: La Hacienda Dover
address: 1171 S Bay Rd, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: This place has a good atmosphere and quite good Mexican style cuisine. The burritos are my favorite, especially with beans and a side of their amazing corn cake. The dessert selection is great too with my favorite being the flash fried cheese cake. The only thing I'd say is not astounding compared to other Mexican restaurants would be their salsas as they just don't quite do it for me as they seem kinda bland compared to other places. But Overall this is a great place to go if you are in the mood for Mexican food.
Waitress was very nice but service was very slow.  Waited over 40 min to get our entrees... place was not busy at all. Good overall was good.

It’s a tough rating for me.  I went 4 stars but was leaning 3.  Pros:   The place was PACKED.  We almost didn’t go in figuring it would be forever.  Not the case.  Quickly seated.  Quick service.  Food came quick.  Servers were attentive and active.  So why leaning 3?   The food.  It was mediocre.  Our group all ordered fajitas.  I mean were they bad?  No.  Were they really good?  No too.  In the end the service bumped it up for me but it’s not a place I would go out of my way to come eat at even with the service.

I'm still surprised by how much the quality of the food and the service fluctuates. I've been here a good number of times and I've had a great experience. But also about half of those visits have been just terrible experiences. If you stick with non-traditional Mexican food, you'll be pretty safe on getting good food. But others are a hit or miss. Like fajitas with nothing but onions as the veggies. Overall this isn't a bad place to visit, but when they charge you 2 dollars extra for hot salsa and don't tell you, it throws you off. It's not the best for the price.

They have parking all around the building. They were busy when I came in, but I still found a spot.
This is a stand alone restaurant that looks like it could've been a fast food joint at one point. The place had quite a few tables and a large bar area. They had a slight wait for tables, but I chose to sit at the bar. The bar had a solid tequila selection of around 50 or so with a good top shelf. The service was top notch, everything I needed I got quickly. The decor was aesthetically pleasing. My only issue was that the floor was a little slippery in my sneakers.

I ordered a Modelo bottle. It was cold and delicious. I also did a couple shots of 1800 which was about $9 a pop. Not terrible, not great.

Chips & Salsa!!!
Chips...solid chip, tasted like it should, and could hold a topping well.
Salsa...the red was chunky and more of a pico, but a bit mushy. The green was a solid tomatillo based salsa, just a little on the tangy side for me.

I ordered Stuffed Jalapenos:Four large jalapeno peppers, hollowed out and filled with our cream cheese mixture, then wrapped in back and broiled. Spicy, creamy, and savory in every bite! $8.99
They weren't wrong in their description. These were delicious, fresh jalapenos, wrapped in bacon. They misspelled bacon on the online menu lol. I was like what is back exactly? They also had a bit of showtime in there, coming out on a sizzling plate. Exciting!!!

I ordered Street Corn: Steamed and grilled corn with mayo, cotija mexican cheese, and chile powder (optional) $3.
The corn was solid, I like it a bit sloppier, but this fulfilled my craving. I go nuts every time I see some sort of elote. I gotta have it!!!

I ordered a tamale, although I don't see it on the online menu. It was chicken with verde sauce and cheese that melted on top. The masa was tasty, almost dry, but not. The chicken inside was good and flavorful. I should've used more sauce on this. I feel like the pork might be an even better choice.

I ordered Tacos Al Pastor: Three tacos filled with our original al pastor seasoned pork, served Mexican taco -stand style. $11.99.
I didn't see an option to get tacos like I normally do, so I went with the Pastor trio.
The pork was seasoned well and delicious. The flour tortilla tried to dry it out, so I used more of the green salsa to combat it. I wasn't asked my preference, I thought "taco stand style" would be corn tortillas. Nopeski! With that being said, they were good on the flavor meter, and loaded with meat.
Beans...chunky texture, nothing special, serviceable.
Rice...soft, fluffy, a little crisp, nothing special to me.

name: Chaiyo Sushi & Thai
address: 1030 Forrest Ave #116, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: I love going to here. The customer service is great. Their service is fast and I've never had a complaint eating here
Took my tiny human here tonight and we are in love. They have a variety of options for various types of eaters. (We are vegetarians and were not disappointed)

I've been meaning to go here for a while and I was certainly not disappointed! The sushi was amazing, and it wasn't overly expensive. They have a wide variety of options, between both the sushi and the Thai food, I'm looking forward to coming back here soon!

Excellent selection of sushi and dishes on the menu, friendly customer service,  and dining experience. I recommend the Pad Thai and anything from the sushi menu! This is one of my go to places for dining out as well as takeout.
Good food and service, reasonable prices.

name: Flavor of India
address: 348 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: We were looking for a vegetarian restaurant and found this restaurant in Dover.   We found the food surprisingly good, perfectly seasoned and prices are affordable.   The only downs the service.   We were the only occupied table for a late lunch and the lone server not only forgot my order but the demeanor is not very welcoming.   He refilled our empty water glasses just when were about finished and getting ready to pay the bill.  The food is good but service  just left a lot to be desired .  I am giving it a three for the food

Fantastic...as usual. Please keep Dover's Indian restaurant- Flavor of India, alive & well as we all strive for the same!
Excellent large menu, rich, delicious flavors, generous portions and fast professional check out!
And if you've never tried it...its the perfect time!
This Indian restaurant serves the greatest Indian cruising in the area. I was very pleased with the service as well as the quality and presentation of the food. Thank you and will revisit again!

I usually reserve my ratings until I've frequented a place at least several times, but this Restaurant deserves a 6 Star rating. It was my only my second visit and the food is absolutely spectacular. The server is immensely attentive to all his customers, and the owner consistently interacts with her customers. BRAVO👏👏👏👏👏👏

I don’t agree with comments that the food is bland.  I enjoy getting take out here.  I stay away from buffets so I can’t rate theirs.  My only complaint would be when I ask for extra spicy, I’d like to feel some burn.  It’s tingly at best.  I plan to continue to eat here even if the food isn’t as hot as I would like.

name: Franco's Pizza & Pasta
address: 1708 E Lebanon Rd, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: The bread was delicious. The pasta was delicious. Everything was delicious. Service was a touch of slow, but the place was busy. Definitely would come back.

This was a great pizzeria! This was my first time here and I am very picky with my Italian food places. The star of our dinner show was a huge Stromboli that was rightfully called "The Works!" This Stromboli was filled with much pizza goodness! It's crispy tasty crust was wrapped around loads of meat, mozzarella cheese and tasty sauce!! Oh yess! So we'll be back to taste more of Franco's menu!

AWESOME FOOD! Served hot from the kitchen. No sitting under heat lamps here, nice, the Italian bread is freshly made on the premises. Couldn't ask for a better meal. I saw some pizzas people ordered that looked delicious! Great service! Generous portions! I ordered linguine in oil and garlic with shrimp, wow I couldn't believe how many shrimp was in this dish. Big portion. Definitely a go to place for Italian food. Hardest working, attentive manager, Marco, I've ever seen. It was busy, he jumped right in, took orders, served. Owners did an excellent job choosing him. We go to Dover every year and last trip found this little gem. I will def stop for dinner again, probably more than once. We LOVED THIS PLACE!!!
I haven't been here in years until recently. Had a look in the kitchen and guys are kicking butt during the lunch rush. The wings and pizza are pretty good.
This place was like a hidden gem. The food is good, the service was friendly, and well priced. You wont be disappointed.

name: Rice Restaurant
address: 45 Greentree Dr, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews:
Such a great recommendation from my brother!

This is some of the best Chinese food I've ever had. The service was prompt and so incredibly respectful and friendly. The food came out promptly and servings were enough to make two meals out of a single order.

I'm a fan of spicy food and the spice here is hot but not in a way that overwhelms the underlying flavors. The sushi was also excellent and tasted fresh and you can even watch the chefs make it in the dining room.

Will definitely return to continue eating my way through the menu.

The owners were very smart for being open on Christmas.  They were the only sit down place open.  The place was packed and I know why..... Food and service were great!!! 
Dining area was cramped, the tables too close so getting in and out of seats were interesting.  Overall very good food, lots of veggies, everyone was happy and not too expensive at all.
Always very fresh and delicious! Their spicy tiger roll and hot lover roll are 2 of our favorites!!
The best sushi I have ever had. My favorite sushi place. Cannot complain about anything. Great food and great service too!!
Rice food was delicious! Presentation was amazing. I didn't think to take other picture but the sushi was amazing.

name: The Countrie Eatery
address: 950 N State St, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: This was a little place we happened upon on our way home from the beach. We stopped for breakfast and it was absolutely delicious. Our waitress was outstanding. She was so friendly and attentive. Always right there to fill the coffee and that place was hopping. My only complaint was the bathroom situation. For a busy place, they only have 1 single bathroom for men and 1 for women, so there was a line. Must be a local favorite since it is a little out of the way, but so busy. I would definitely go back again.

This place was not good. The only good thing about it was the size of the portions but the flavor was off. The problem with the eggs is that they were overcooked and under seasoned. The potatoes had no seasoning. One of our family members got a chip beef waffle and it literally came with 2 tablespoons of chipped beef. There were so many flies in the dining area that I felt like I kept swatting at them. The inside was very dated and dirty. I don't understand why people are giving this place such good reviews. One thing that was nice is outside there is a little overlooked that allows you to feed the fish below. That was fun. But I review based on food and restaurant and this place has a lot of opportunities for growth.

Service was exceptionally good and the liver and onions are to die for! The red snapper was perfect. The crab cakes have a little too much filler for me, but I usually make my own and dont use any filler. I'd go back again.

Please do not eat anything other than breakfast here! The seafood is frozen and was served semi-raw. The scallops were chewy with NO flavor. The crab cake and stuffed shrimp were also completely filled with bread. Both the manager and server were not very apologetic about our experience and was told “dont worry about it”, when requesting a partial refund.

If you are in Dover, this is the place to start your mornings, take a break for lunch, or settle back and enjoy a peaceful evening dinner. On our five day trip to visit family, we enjoyed two meals here. Breakfast and lunch helped to make our trip to Dover a most memorable trip. The breakfast for me consisted of scrambled eggs, french toast, and bacon. Simple items but they were darn near perfect! Both visits we were blessed to have excellent service! This place is not to be missed if you are in Dover! Enjoy the wildlife on the mini deck overlooking Silver Lake too! The kids will love it...

name: MISSION BBQ
address: 365 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Great flavors, great menu, great selections and GREAT customer service! The Slow cooked Beef Brisket is to die for, it melts in your mouth. The sweet potatoes, mac n cheese and Sweet Tea set it off 😋

This location catered food at my place of employment the end of last year and it tasted amazing. I went on 2/15/20 and had the pulled pork, pulled chicken, Cole slaw and green beans and was totally disappointed. I'm about to toss the rest of the food because I'm not going to eat it. So disappointed. I guess it depends on the person. My friend had the ribs and he thoroughly enjoyed them. Try it for yourself. Great cause so I'll continue to support them occasionally.

OMG!! What is not good about this place?! I don't know! Everything was delicious, the ribs were just like they are supposed to, falling off the bone. The brisk was tender and delicious. The sausage was good... The mac and cheese 🤯🤯🤯🤯!!! The string beans were really good also. The Turkey sandwich delish, even thought it looked dry, but it wasn't! The corn cake was one of the best! The pull pork was so flavorful. Also, I loved almost all of the BBQ sauces they had. I cannot forget about the staff!!! The best customer service I have had in such a long time. They were all so wonderful. I somehow wished I lived here to have it again. Love this place.

Excellent all around!  The Cashier was friendly and helpful, the prep guy was great and they brought out desserts for us since it was our first time there.  Great food, great service, will absolutely come back.

I’d give it 100 stars! Perfectly cooked and prepared. Minimal wait after order at register. Seating in clean rustic canteen style with ample seasonings and paper towels at each table. Much genuine military and responders memorabilia displayed throughout.

name: McGlynn's Pub & Restaurant
address: 800 N State St, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews:
Would definitely come back here. Food was very good and our waitress was friendly and attentive. The hostess, not so much, but that was a one minute contact until we got seated. Nice view onto lake. 
Stuffed meatballs and roasted corn appetizer. Jambalaya and Kitchen Sink burger for entrées. All were very good. Restrooms clean and attended. When we went the bar area was "buzzing" so it might be a little difficult for anyone with hearing sensitivities. Many menu options including entrées, burgers, sandwiches, and salads.
We love McGlynn's! Great food and specials. Attentive staff. You will enjoy the view.

Food is great, Service is even better, location is amazing during the day and if you can see Silver Lake, decor and atmosphere are amazing.  My only gripe...As someone of Irish blood, is one would think that a place that has an Irish name, Irish decor and themes; that they would serve more typical Irish food. Guinness Lamb stew, corned beef,  Shepard's pot pie, potato and leek soup.  But no, I see nachos, fish tacos, burgers, and bourbon on the salmon. Don't get me wrong, what they make is really good, and worth going back for more. It just doesnt fit. I think a menu revamp would serve this place well.

The Kitchen Sink burger is big and very tasty with lots of toppings. The colossal crab sandwich was good but I wouldn't call it colossal. Could have definitely eaten another one to be satisfied. Good selection of drinks and free popcorn. Great location right on the water!

Had the kitchen sink burger, some Yuengling and plenty of local entertainment in the form of fights and singing. DJ was pretty good too. We got in late and needed some food, everyone's was pretty decent and didn't take very long considering it was a Friday night and the bar was packed. There was however a nice fight that broke out, barf in the bathroom, and some pretty rowdy patrons but hey, it's a bar. We had fun. Food was good. Would go back

name: Kabab Korner
address: 706 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Surprisingly surprising! I call it no2 my happy place. It is small but Service is amazing, Dennis is the man!! Very skilled chef and he would try to please you as much as possible if you want to mix match from the menu. I LOVE THE CHICKEN CURRY, ALWAYS THE SAME!! People drive by because of the location on main road but definitely worth the stop. Food leaves your stomach warm and full. Completely listen to the server's suggestions on what to order. Quickly became a favorite place for my husband and I to have a lovely quiet meal. What I would call a diamond in the rough.
This place is surely go to without a shadow of doubt. The best served Chicken Manchuria in the US so far. I have lost count how many times I have had it in last 3-4 years.
I really loved this place. The food was great and the staff friendly. I'll be going back soon!

Really good food!  I always get the chicken kabob wraps or ginger chicken w/ rice.  The chutney sauce sets it OFF.  The prices are very affordable, if you dine in, service can be slow but take out is prompt.

This last experience was disappointing. The Chicken Tikka Kabab were NOT fresh. It was little cold in the middle and had no taste and flavor. The worst thing, it was cold from center and was definitely made from frozen premade. 
I'll be honest and upfront. I visited this place almost 3 yrs ago and it was not like this. The kebabs I ordered were freshly made and had very good flavor. 
They are adding an Indian grocery store to this restaurant.
I hope they will improve on their food preparation and maintain a better quality fresh product.

name: Bangkok Thai Cuisine
address: 266 S Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Every single food item we ordered was amazing! Tofu was perfect, real crab meat in the fried rice, and tempura veggies! Yuuuuummmmm😍😍😍😍😍 service was out of this world! Thank you Nicole ❤️ you are the best!
My father found this little hole in the wall and I couldn't have been happier! Food came with good sized portions and the beer was actually pretty good! Definitely recommend!

Food was good yet service was not. I had ordered some mussels and yet they did not come out until after a regular came in ordered and he had his soup before I even had my mussels and his food came out before I even got my soup. He had really good fast service while I had slow. He was give a condiments try full of sauces. I had to ask for one.

Some of the best Thai food around. Thai food is one of my favorite cuisines and I have favorite restaurants in San Diego and DC. This compares with any major city in quality. Small town vibes and very friendly service. I love this place. 
The duck is amazing
Pineapple fried rice with lamb
Ginger with beef
Family really enjoyed their meals, and my wife loves the bubble (boba) tea.

name: Speedway Cafe
address: 737 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Stopped in tonight to try their new vegan options. The Italian sausage on flat bread with the peppers and onions was very tasty. Super glad to see a local establishment now offering vegan options. They've added even more to their new vegan menu, and the Gyro was amazing!

Food and service were fantastic! First time here glad we didn't wait any longer we will surely be back. Prices are certainly reasonable especially with the amount of food served. Only thing I would tweek is the creamed chipped beef gravy.... not a whole lot of flavor lil more seasoning and it'd be on point 😉
The food is typically good but it's not always the cleanest place. They offer inexpensive breakfast specials most of the week and the staff is always friendly.

My new favorite place to eat in Dover. Colleen has become our favorite server, just a very pleasant person! Food tastes home made and huge portions! You know it has to be good because I rarely give out 5 stars so you know they deserve it. I am moving to Dover soon and I'm looking forward to being able to stop by there and becoming a regular diner here.
That 5 egg omelet is spectacular! Can't say enough about it.  The wait staff is exemplary.

name: Grotto Pizza
address: 1159 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Great pizza with an adjacent sports bar. They could do better with keep the place clean (lots of trash on the floor). Overall they have excellent service. Plus their bartender had a heavy pour which was great.

I was at the bar in this review but the bar staff were very friendly and attentive. Wasn't a second that my cup was empty without someone making sure I was okay. Ordered some tenders afterwards and they were fresh and hot.

 Definitely coming back and should to James for helping out the bar staff and making my experience even better!

Wow!  The Mama Grotto Pizza is so good.  I never knew there was such a pizza.  It's just delicious.  Thank you for fast, efficient, and friendly service.  The store was very clean and Tonya was quite helpful giving me plenty of napkins, plates, and packets of parmesan cheese.  The restroom was spotless.  Thank you Grottos for my beach experience in March.

I just had to laugh at our experience. Stopped in on the way to the beach as it was late evening and we wanted our favorite pizza. 4 tables total occupied in restaurant, we were seated, 2 employees passed by us probably 20 times neither one saying a word or looking at us. Waited 20 minutes for a girl to say she would be right with us (same one that kept waiting table right behind us). She knew we were ready to walk out. Big mistake coming here, pizza was delicious so that's why I gave it a star but wish I could give negatives. What we hoped to be a semi short stop, ended up an hour. No sense in complaining to staff because they all stood around on phones or talking, obviously didn't care to check on us. I have NEVER  seen a popcorn machine this dirty, looks like it caught fire..nope..girl closed up machine for the night and left it as is. Never EVER will go back to this one, this location gives Grotto's a bad look!! Visited 7/17/19. 8pm

While on our way to a wedding in DE, we decided, on a whim, to give Grotto Pizza a try for lunch. The atmosphere of the restaurant was very family friendly! An open, spacious dining room, arcade/game room for kids, and a bar for the adults. 
Pizza was the obvious choice for lunch, as I was anxious to give it a try for the first time. Unfortunately, it didn't pass the test for a decent pizza pie. The crust was too soft and undercooked. A bit more crispy would have been ideal. The sauce wasn't bad, but it definitely wasn't anything that stood out. The biggest "killer" for me was the over abundance of cheese. Way too much, to where the pizza was loaded with grease, and it almost made it difficult to swallow without the cheese getting stuck in my throat. 
I'm sure it's a great pizza for the locals and that is absolutely fine. But I've had excellent pizza in my travels, and unfortunately  Grotto Pizza is not one of them.

name: Hibachi Japanese Steak House
address: 691 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: We always have a great time at the Hibachi Japanese Steak House.  They have great specials for lunch on the weekend.  The service and food we're both fantastic.

Overall a fun and delicious experience. We were seated relatively quickly, and we got our drinks and salads within just a couple minutes. The salads were fantastic, but the sodas were just seltzer water, without syrup.the waitress was friendly and understanding, and brought out fresh drinks. I ordered the crunchy spicy California roll which was delicious. The Hibachi chef was friendly, and good at what he does. The chicken and shrimp combo was delicious. I am only giving 4 stars because I (and it seemed like other patrons) was uncomfortably hot. Hibachi places tend to be warmer, but this place more so. I also give 4/5 as the price tag was a bit higher than what I have seen at other hibachi places for a nearly identical meal.

Well you know I say it as it is. This is a good restaurant with good tasty food! A little pricey but good things come at a price I love the Tat roll and I got shrimp  and scallops habachi which was also tasty. Portions was reasonable I am not sure if it's the same for take out as I eat in. Overall  you should visit. You wont regret it!
Great service. Excellent meal.

I love their salad and house dressing.  I would go there just to eat that. Their steak and shrimp is delicious. We were served with an abundance of good and it was so good. The rice was very good too.

name: Diamond State Grill
address: 913 S Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: This is a locals place. But they welcome visitors all the time. It’s owned by a hard working local couple who welcome everyone. I eat here often, they know their clientele and the food is homemade. They do get busy at times since many enjoy eating there. Don’t give the negative reviews any thought. No matter where you go someone will always complain or inappropriate allegation. If you want good home cooked food in a casual atmosphere you can’t go wrong.
Food is topnotch. Very friendly staff. I like going there
I really like this place for breakfast! Their french toast are DELICIOUS! And their pancakes are huge!! Their food is not greasy at all and the waitresses are very friendly!
We were in the Dover area and we're looking for somewhere to eat breakfast. And found this place.  Food was good and prices were great. Service was quick and friendly.

Amount of food compared to price is on point! Waitress was awesome, very attentive. Owner/cook noticed hubby and I were under the weather and before we left, sent us home with a huge container of their homemade chicken and pasta soup...NO CHARGE!! The soup was delicious. Sounds crazy but when you don't feel good, it was like having your mom take care of you when you were little. Made us feel like we were family. 😊

name: Governors Cafe
address: 144 Kings Hwy SW, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Sitting on the front porch on a clear spring day with fully blooming trees and the scent of fresh flowers:PERFECT!  What an historic and significant setting for a restaurant. We had salads that were tasty and served quickly for our executive lunch on a weekday. Asparagus and chicken that was tender and covered with pesto. This is a new favorite place for me in Dover. The room with the Governor pictures is awesome!
I went there for a prime rib sandwich and a side of potato salad.  It was delicious.  The people there are supportive of active and retired military as well.  Very nice staff.

Great spot for lunch. Cozy atmosphere, good menu with good prices. Staff always pleasant and attentive. Outside seating during warmer months. Parking can be an issue, but that's anywhere in downtown Dover. Highly recommend.

Very unique atmosphere with a lot of beautiful wood decor and large fireplace. Can't say everyday that you dined in an old governor's mansion either. There's a restaurant, bar area and a little coffee shop/cafe. The food is pretty tasty and reasonably priced. Vegetable portions are oddly skimpy. Service is friendly and quick.
Atmosphere is nice, there is an inside and outside seating area. Food is ok. Nothing amazing there yet which is why I gave 4 stars. They have good options though and a full bar.

name: El Nopal
address: 627 W Division St, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: This amazing place to eat.. the food is delicious but don't plan on fine dining or a dining experience....it's a very small home converted into a restaurant and they serve food on paper products..  But don't let that discourage you from trying this place...
Food was decent. All of the food is freshly made. Guacamole is the best!
The food here is so great! I've never been disappointed, the Steak tacos are my fav

Delicious authentic Mexican food from Sinaloa region. Very cheap tacos, fajitas, beans, quesadillas, etc. Variety of nice hot sauces to add to your food as well. Filling plates and lots of good options. They also have a case filled with good Mexican sort drinks and a counter with lots of Mexican deserts and candies. Definitely a good experience!

Very friendly service and usually seems busy with multiple take out orders.
I went here and had a pretty big order. I recieved all my food hot and quickly cooked. I will definitely be going back. Thanks!

name: El Azteca Authentic Mexican Restaurant
address: 859 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Good service, good food and clean tables. Prices are good overall and the portions have always been impressive. The owner is usually there and it shows in the quality of the staff. They're friendly and always helpful the several times I've been.

Great Mexican food. Generous portions at an amazing price. I had the Grande Special dinner plate. It is somewhat of a sampler of sorts. Best bang for your buck in my opinion. Two plates worth of food for 12 bucks. Can't beat it.
Food is always delicious and cooked fresh, also very good and polite customer service
Great food! Good prices! Friendly staff! Delicious margaritas!
I took the whole family here this weekend. I was very impressed. We were seated quickly, received our meals in a timely manner and enjoyed the experience. The food was very tasty. We will be back!

name: Pizza Delight By Giacomo
address: 67 Greentree Dr, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: It was tasty.  It was a pretty standard pizza shop cheesesteak.  Big, 16 in, it probably would have fit nicely on a 14-inch roll.  I am very happy with my $14.75 total price for a 16-inch cheese steak and a draft of beer.  I don't know, I do know, I'm nitpicking but I would rather a full 14 in than an emtpy’ish 16 inch roll.  The pizzas look really good.  Good overall experience.

The jumbo shrimp is only the size of a quarter, and was overcooked. The chicken fingers were overcooked. The containers were caved in because they were cheap aluminum. The calzone was put on a thin paper plate and shoved in the bag with the sauce. Tasted okay. The pizza was just okay, not great. I don't know why anyone would want to wait so long for this. Pretty pricey for the quality.
Food, Service,and prices are excellent. The owner still visits each table to chat and make sure everything is good.

This place has a nice variety of comfort foods on the menu.  I had a fried shrimp basket and was delighted to see that I could get onion rings instead of fries at no additional charge......... under $10. My companion had a chicken fingers basket and that chicken had big fingers... More like large chicken tenders. He said the fries were delicious. Our friend had pasta and cheese baked dish... I think it was stuffed shells. It was quite a nice serving and cake with salad and bread. She took half of it pasta home because it was just too much. I believe her dish was about $13. As we we're leaving we saw people eating pizza. Boy, that looks delicious too. And since we used to eat at their other location which is now closed, we know how good it is. We'll be back.

This has got to be the best pizza place in Dover! We are a family from Connecticut and New York so we know our pizza and this was spot on!!  I don't know what one reviewer was talking about with her racist comments because when we went there the place was packed for dining and the take out line was out the door; all walks of life were in there AND NOBODY WAS TREATED DIFFERENTLY.  The staff was extremely busy yet friendly and the kitchen was clean.  This is now our go to pizza place!!!

name: La Tonalteca Mexican Restaurant
address: 245 S Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews:
My wife and I walked in a half an hour before their buffet ended. When we told the man at the reception what we wanted he gave us a quizzical look and said he would have to talk to the manager. 
 Mind you there are less than 10 other customers in the restaurant at this time. We waited 5 minutes for her to come out and say she didn't want to make any more buffet food so they wouldn't give it to us. 
 So then we tell them we want to do normal dine in. They say ok and then we wait a few more minutes as they show each other some stuff on their phones before the man sighs, grabs 2 menus, walks us over to a booth in the corner and quickly drops the menus on the end of the table, spins on his heel and walks away without a word. We waited close to 10 minutes at the booth without anyone bringing us water or asking for our order before we got up and walked out.

Wow, delicious food!  And large portions.  Stopped for Iunch while Christmas shopping and had a great meal.  The atmosphere is really unique, inside and out.  The waiter was very attentive, and the food was served fast.  Everything was warm and fresh, and of course warm tortilla chips & salsa.  We will definitely be back.

This place closed down for a little bit or an unfortunate incident but the place looks amazing now you can tell they have up their game and straightened everything out love the food here love the atmosphere of the staff is very friendly they always give us exactly what we order we like to customize our orders a little bit and they always seem to get it right amazing Place recommend everyone to eat here...

I was walking by this restaurant where the sign caught my eyes about tacos Monday. I was like great it’s Mexican and also I never had a taco! I went inside the restaurant and told the guy I would like to try the tacos also I never had a taco! Hoping that they will make a good first impression however I was seated then got a bowl of chips and sauce which was lovely. My tacos came out and I was like what?? I could have done this myself it was horrible! Not what I expected.

I had canitas and it was delicious. The margarita was so good I had to get another one 😂. Hubby is driving me home 🤗. Hubby had entree# 234.I had a taste of his chicken and shrimp. It was nicely seasoned and tender

name: Great Wall Kitchen
address: 425 S New St, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: Wow! We just moved from new york and were skeptical about the quality of their food, boy were we surprised! This place is amazing! The food was so fresh and flavorful! The best egg drop soup, fried rice, general Taos chicken, chicken mai fun, and boneless spare ribs. Oh and the spring rolls were delicious!! This is now our go to Chinese food place *NOTE they only take cash and it's not in the best area BUT everyone was friendly.

One Of The Best Chinese Food Dover has to offer. Always fresh. Best chicken hands down. No Chinese store in Dover can compare on certain dishes. Been coming here since I was a kid. CONSISTENCY at its finest!! Go back to five wings.
Fast, good food ,good price ,nice staff,clean place
Tried the general tso's chicken, hot and sour soup, and the chicken wings. All were average.

First off, out the gate... the location man o man. They don't accept card, cash only. I read all the reviews and it took me 5 yrs after being a resident in the city to finally get some. 

I went with the sesame chicken and the wings, FIRE! The portions go crazy! Overall the taste was decent whole time but the prices are a bit steep. Be safe when going, a bit sketchy but good food.

name: Carter's Restaurant
address: 2 S Governors Ave, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: Carters Restaurant has and always be the best place for down home good food ever since I was in elementary school.

This place is historic. Yes the decor is not the greatest. But most whole in the walls have no decor. Go, be nice to Ms. Carter, you'll enjoy your meal and keep it moving. I ordered fish platter with candied sweets and collards. It was great.
The fried fish sandwich is delicious,  the greens and mac n cheese is good too
IM SORRY I HAVENT TRIED THIS RESTAURANT SOONER. IVE LEAVED HERE 20+ YRS AND IM JUST NOW FINDING OUT HOW GREAT THIS FOOD IS!!!! MS CARTER YOU PUT YOUR WHOLE FOOT IN THESE GREENS AND FISH
I always get the fish platter when I order from here. They give me a nice size platter! Good food and seasoned well!

name: Chick-fil-A
address: 1440 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Had a bad day at work on a Friday and decided to pick up dinner.  The staff was so friendly and upbeat. Really elevated my mood. I hope that I can one day provide this level of service to lift someone up

Staff is friendly, genuine and warm. The food is not fast food but it's fast. I was surprised at the efficiency. I don't eat fast food at all and it was delish! And I really like that they are closed on Sundays, the Sabbath. That is awesome.
Great service, very active managers, and extremely fast and friendly associates.

The drive-thru line went all the way through their parking lot and I was still in and out in less than 10 minutes! The employees were very pleasant and extremely efficient. Everything in my order was perfect. I would strongly recommend.
Dover Air force Base is not the only military installation in this town. Chick-fil-A operates with military precision to deliver, On Time and On Target, the Lord's Chicken.

name: LongHorn Steakhouse - Curbside To Go Available
address: 505 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: We always enjoy going to Longhorn but tonight was especially wonderful. It is our sons birthday. I didn't even tell the waitress, she must have heard. When desert was brought, my son's plate had a birthday candle and it made his whole night. Even another server who was not assigned to our table stopped to recommend good dishes and chat. It was an all around great experience! I recommend.

Okay, no judgement please! I come to Longhorn once a week and seriously they are amazing. The Manager Steve really has the place flowing. Stop by and make sure you ask for Steve. Don’t forget to order some bites.

Ted Kelly
We just ordered and ate! The cook is phenomenal,best tasting steak, Mac & cheese, bread good even cold. U like it done right this cook at 4pm is on the money. The chicken tenders are luscious. The salad is a real one weight & content, not the yellow ends of lettuce, cheese. I’ve never been disappointed the 3rd visit I’ve made.

My husband and I ate here tonight around dinner hour. 

The good- we were seated within 5 minutes(now we know why they weren't busy), and our waitress was friendly. The appetizer was good as well.

The bad- we waited a long time for our dinners to come out. I ordered chicken with asparagus and tomato, and literally had two tomatoes and two pieces of asparagus on top my chicken. It came out cold. Additionally,  my broccoli was raw......
My husband ordered a steak and fries, and salad. The salad was good. The steak and fries were barely warm. The steak was thin, about half as thick as one from the texas roadhouse, and then once home he has had bad heartburn tonight.

All in all, do not recommend,  and we won't be back. Two stars ONLY because our waitress tried! Even she felt bad when she saw we barely touched our food.....and are out $68........
Great food with excellent service!

name: US 13 Grill & Catering
address: 1115 S Governors Ave, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: We have been here several times and have never been disappointed.  The food is excellent  and the service was very good. The price is also very reasonable. I highly recommend this restaurant and I will be back in the future.
The place is not too big bit it is well kept.  Nick was a phenomenal waiter. The food is good, presented well and not greasy. Price was just fair. Definitely will come back.

My husband took me here today and I was thrilled. It was like a diner that reminded me of my home back in Pittsburgh. You can tell the crowd was somewhat full of regulars. I had a delicious omelet that wasn't over cooked and the potatoes are homemade(not shredded)  the coffee is never ending and our waitress very pleasant. The prices are fair also!!!! I am glad we went!!! I am looking forward to going back!!!!!

Nice menu, variety of specials, clean and comfortable dining room, great service, very reasonable prices. The breakfast foods offered from open to close are always hot and delicious. (There's a 10% senior discount, but not on breakfast.)
The breakfast was outstanding.   The staff was friendly and did an awesome job.   Loved it.   Very nice inside.   Very reasonable priced.

name: Touchdown Restaurant
address: 1666 S Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: I Ordered the ham dinner for myself and my daughter, our Easter dinner.  It was abdolutely delicious!  Rich, creamy mac and cheese, green beans seasoned perfectly and yummy sweet potatoes,   oh yes, ham...not too.salty, just perfect.  And dessert for later, cheesecake. Plenty of leftovers!!  Thanks guys for helping us make today special!   Paula, "Another Modelo please!"
Great food. Plenty of room on the holiday weekend. DJ was good. Drink specials we're a big hit.
Karaoke fun 😁 and wings

The Waitresses are very friendly and they greet you as soon as you walk in, they bring you your food and drink before you even know it. The food is great and not overly priced. You can watch your favorite team play or you can watch all the games. If your team is not doing so well they got a pool table so you can play pool. The atmosphere is so great I've been going there for two years now. It's a wonderful place where everybody knows everybody,  it's like the TV show Cheers.

Solid bar if you're out of town on a football Sunday and need somewhere to watch the game. There is a decent contingent of Buffalo Bills supporters as it's the local Bills backer bar. There are also a lot of Ravens, Eagles, and Washington fans, which makes sense considering the proximity. 

Food was pretty standard fare for a bar that knows what it is. Above average wings, respectable appetizer selection that comes across as competent. 

They have the room to accommodate the crowd on a Sunday afternoon. Which means it comes off as roomy and comfortable on days when they aren't as busy.

name: Betsy Ross Pizza
address: 1294 Forrest Ave, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: I told my friends about this place with my highest recommendations. I  go to this restaurant often. This recommendation is always successful. The dishes they serve are fantastic and the crew is attentive and cooperative. always when we go to this place we enjoy a gorgeous time.  I warmly recommend this restaurant.
Excellent burgers and a yummy meatball sub. And the complimentary chicken soup is a hit every time. Thanks Mrs. T for the excellent service.

Best deals ever.  Nowhere else across the US have I found a deal as amazing as their 24 wing and lg pizza deal.   For $25 you get 24 actual wings, not the winglets some major companies pass off, as well as a delicious original recipe pizza.   My favorite place since I was a child.

My department just had some food catered for our nightshift. It was hot and delicious! We had so much food we were able to feed our whole team and some. It was delicious and no doubt we will be ordering again! And a huge shootout to the owner and workers who were just the best!!
My wife and I enjoy eating here all the time! Their food is always good!

name: QDOBA Mexican Eats
address: 1211 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Always a great experience at Qdoba. Very pleasant staff and excellent food for a reasonable price. Get the app to save.
I live this food. The atmosphere is great. You can chill and relax while you eat.

I go to Qdoba about once a month. My family loves the tacos and nacho bowls. The customer service was amazing!! Dan, Renee and Hannah made every customer feel special.  All the workers there had great teamwork.
This place is worth trying. They have big portions for convenient rates. Constantly well kept and with excellent mood. Will visit here again.
Try their impossible bowl and it’s really good with that tortilla soup and it’s a must try one in Qdoba and it’s a very nice option for vegans and especially for Indians.

name: Pho Viet
address: 155 N Dupont Hwy Ste. 4, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: This is a nice quaint Vietnamese restaurant located on Dupont hwy in Dover, DE. As a newbie to Vietnamese cuisine, I truly did enjoy my meal. First dish out was my appetizer, a nice fresh Shrimp Spring roll that was partnered with a delicious peanut sauce. I choose to order Pho combo # 2. This was a full bowl of rice noodles, mildly flavored Vietnamese beef broth that was boasting with tenderloin steak, brisket, tendon and meatball. My taste buds have now been officially elevated and I certainly will return!

Visited here last week and the Pho is delicious! The broth has good flavor and there are sauces available if you want to spice it up. They bring out a plate of bean sprouts and basil to add as well. This bowl is a medium on their menu. The portions are very generous. Staff are friendly.

The portions are really large, even medium sizes. I ordered a Beef broth soup. I started eating at 11:50am. It’s 12:22pm now and the bowl is practically full.

The spring rolls are awesome too. I wish the music was more traditional Vietnamese.

I’d come again.

Now this is a noodle place but that's not what I had. Pineapple fried rice w/ chicken caught my eye and I had to try it and egg roles. Loved it! The restaurant was very clean, service was busy but on top of things. Everything came out on time and very well presented. Servings are very large I'm looking forward to my left over. My wife did have the noodle bowl and loved it to. Definitely recommend giving this place a try. Cheers! 🍻

We recently stopped in at Pho Viet on our way home from visiting Wilmington, Delaware. It's conveniently located just a few minutes off the highway and there's plenty of parking in the back. We grabbed a seat inside, ordered the vegetarian (tofu) spring roll as an appetizer and then got two entrees. Caroline got lemongrass chicken and I got chicken pho. Both were delicious. The pho broth was perfectly seasoned and salty and the portion of noodles and chicken was generous. It was also piping hot and came with fresh basil and sprouts. The lemongrass chicken was a high quality cut of chicken and also super flavorful. The staff is super friendly and eager to help. We'd definitely make a return visit. It was awesome. Next time we go I think we'd try one of the Louisiana/New Orleans specialty items on the menu.

name: The Boulevard Live Entertainment Restaurant
address: 1036 Lafferty Ln, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: It was my first time being at this place. I had fun. The drinks were fantastic. I enjoyed the music. Nice crowd.
Very elegant and convenient place. They offer big meals and for fair prices. I loved the meals very much and the staff were super affable and chatty. Will definitely recommend this place.

This was my first visit to see Mike Philly Jazz concert on Valentines day. Tickets were $55. The Jazz show was remarkable, one of the greatest shows I've seen!! The food was tasty. However, I waited 2 hours and 30 minutes to get my food and my husband order was incorrect and he waited and additional 30 minutes. Then when he recieved his food...they ran out of the vegetable he ordered. No exaggeration it was unbelievable and disaster experience!
Attentive Bartenders, great food and the vibe is everything.  Meant the owner and he is man of good character.  We will be back and bringing friends
The best 30 and over club and great bar and grill around. Want grown and sexy  the boulevard is where to be.

name: Chaiyo Sushi & Thai
address: 1151 E Lebanon Rd, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Commercialized atmosphere. Food was good but average. If I could give the customer service and waitress a rating a 5 I would. They were wonderful. They made up most of the stars on this rating.

Ordered online for delivery and food came over 20 minutes past the ETA. While that may or may not have been the restaurants fault, once we finally got out order, we were missing food. I called the restaurant 20 times.. (not exaggerating) and didn’t get an answer. I guess we’re just out the money? I honestly feel robbed.
Food was awesome. Service was awesome.

Had 2 bad points.  First, the ordering “online” system had an Issue and my order was not ready when I got there.  Also, when I got home, realized that the curries did not have the proteins in the curry.  Didn’t get any comp for food being late either.  The curry itself, spring rolls, and the  crab rangoons were good.  But won’t recommend doing the online service.

Absolutely great food. Me and my wife we in town for 5 days and we came here 3 times.  And it got better each time.

Drunken noodles were amazing, and the red curry was great.  Spicy tuna tempura roll was the first spicy tuna I've had that actually had some kick to it and it was fantastic.

name: El Pipil Restaurant
address: 720 Townsend Blvd, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Nice little place, food was excellent, decor was nice. Would definitely recommend. Food was fresh and authentic. Not very busy but should have been prices were reasonable. Staff were nice and fun
Excellent food and love the environment. My family lives right up the street and I don't know how I've driven past for so many years without stopping. It's a weekly visit for my girlfriend and I now.

Ok, El Pipil Restaurant (pronounced Pee-Peel)(I know, funny, right!? I bet you will always remember it that way...lol) anyways, it is not visible from the main road but if you are near Lowe's Dover search "latino food" and it should pop out on the first 5 searches. The food was very good as it looks in the pictures, lots of flavors and spicy if you wanted it spicy. Since we went late at night there was almost no wait time. The tables are lovely decorated with beautiful carvings resembling typical scenarios of latin culture and don Freddy is wonderful host (as long as he is not busy :) but he'll always try to please you)
They serve large portions and for convenient prices. super nice staff members. Will visit again.
The food here is always amazing. Definitely a diamond in the rough. The most authentic you can get

name: Outback Steakhouse
address: 1574 N Dupont Hwy Ste. 800, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Very good right from the door. I don't think I've ever ordered food served looking exactly like the photo on the menu until now. Delicious and served fast... Loved the atmosphere and the wait staff was very friendly...
Food was great. Service was excellent even though they were busy. They gave us enough time to eat our salads before bringing out the main course, which is a very underrated skill. Thanks
Great bar staff food was tasty and came out quickly! Complementary desert for my birthday

Outback is a great chain restaurant. One thing I can say from a couple experiences at this location. If you have an issue with your food manager will come to your table. They will work until it's to your satisfaction and take care of you. Very courteous and professional.  Not something that is practiced well today. Thanks Outback and your wonderful staff!

I went for my 42 birthday. Waited 2 1/2 hours to be sat. What does call ahead seating do for for parties of 8 or more if they aren't gonna have a table prepared for that many people you call for? Seriously!!!!!

name: Pats Select Pizza l Grill
address: 1224 Forrest Ave, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: Had the best service and super customer oriented experience! I placed a large order and the guy helping me was beyond helpful at checking the accuracy of my order. I forgot one part of my order and staff member came out and reminded me! Very appreciative of their patience and helpfulness.

I normally like places that aren't chains when it comes to pizza, but this place is pretty good. I haven't had anything here that I didn't like. It's all good. I really like their appetizer egg roll cheesesteak! The pizza is good too.

okay so I've been here two times. I can't even begin to express how much I love this place. The food is so good. It's always fresh. The salads are phenomenal. There are plenty of salads to choose from and I'm not talking about your average garden salad. Pretty much something. The dressings match the sounds perfectly. When you get the food it actually looks like the pics from the menu. The establishment is always clean the staff are always very friendly and they never botch my order regardless if I'm ordering for 2 or 6. It's fairly new so it's common for new restaurants to provide outstanding service. let's just hope in time that everything remains the same and I will remain a customer because I recommend this place to lot of friends I've even been here with my family two out of the three times and they love it and the elderly people in my family are really picky so gold 🌟 😉 KEEP UP THE GOOD WORK! PS-the prices are slightly higher than the average pizza place but this isn't your average Pizza joint so I think its right on the money!

I hadn't been to this Pat's in 4 years. We took 3 of our grandchildren there last night. I was pleasantly surprised by the improvements in decor, menu, quality of food and service. Our server was Kristen. She was personable and attentive and did a great job.  The food was very good. I will definitely go back.  I reserve 5 stars for high end dining experiences so a 4 star rating is a top rating for Pat's from me.
Super friendly staff, resturant was spotless, food was excellent and reasonably priced. Highly recommend the shrimp and crab bisque.

name: Simaron Pizza & Steak Shop
address: 415 W Loockerman St, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: Really good food. Amazing service. I highly recommend.
Discovered this place a few months ago and have been going back a few times a week . Great menu and staff. Looking forward to tasting more of their menu. 🙂

They cook and serve free Thanksgiving dinners.  They also make a very good cheesesteak.  Pretty cool grandmother eclectic mix of stuff hanging on the walls.  The three people behind the counter seemed to be getting along very well as they cranked out a lot of food at 10:30 a.m. on a Saturday morning in January in Dover.  The other half of this Cheesesteak was hard to give away but the person I gave it to was very excited to have it so that eased my pain, a little.  Great overall experience.  Yes, they got some well deserved ‘Great People’ points.
OMG the portions. The quality. The selection. The cops eat here so you know it's good. Don't order if you're not hungry. You'll have leftovers. The cheese steaks are the best in Dover. Period.

Just finished a cheese steak from here. I ordered on line for pick up thru Grubhub. 
It’s been a while but seemed better than I remembered. One of the best I’ve had from anywhere in a long time.
Probably the best in Dover. Service was fast and very friendly.

name: King Buffet
address: 293 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews:
Great restaurant!
Very cheap!
Great service.
Delicious food!
Amazing atmosphere. 
I travel a lot, and it’s one of the best places to eat ever! 
Everything time my family comes here we have a great experience!

This is surely one of the finest restaurants in the neighborhood. Always when I visit this place I am so pleased. They keep their very high  level service and the highest level of cooking  they serve. You are always happy with this restaurant. Warmly  recommended.

My experience at King buffet was GREAT.  I love the atmosphere and the employees are so nice and caring.  Maggie ALWAYS seems to come check on her customers to make sure everything is ok.  I have seen her go out of her way to make sure things are right.  Thank you for the great service that you give.

DO NOT EAT HERE!!!. I expected a restaurant with an average of 4.3 stars to be at least acceptable. King buffet left a bland taste in my mouth with their old and dry assortments of Western dishes. If the owners focused more on affordable Chinese dishes instead of seafood and American dishes then the quality of food will skyrocket as well as keeping food costs down. People are going to take advantage of buffet crab legs as much as possible (even the employees seem to hoard the crab) so save your some money and focus on stocking up fresh, easy, cheaper, and delicious foods that people actually expect from a Chinese buffet. If the food wasn't dry and the assortment more focused then I would visit here again. Please save yourself some time and do not eat here, there's many more options for Chinese here in Dover.

I've been coming to this place since I was a child. Maggie is such a great host she makes you feel welcomed and part of her family. She always greets everyone with a smile and assist with any issues if abay.
Great food and just a great atmosphere

name: Tropical Delight Cafe
address: 1156 S Bay Rd, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews:
How do I begin? -☆

 I research restaurants before I go in hopes that I'm able to find something good especially since there are not a lot of places in our area. Based on the reviews we willingly  drove 30 minutes away from our home.   I called ahead to ask if they had oxtails. We were told they were in the process of cooking the food  that was at 3:14.  We arrived at 4:08. Walked in very excited as we saw people waiting in line for their food. When we spoke the the lady taking orders we explained that we called ahead for the food and arrived within the time she said it would be done. 1 hour and 22 minutes later  ( I watched two episodes of love it or list it watched countless people come and go In the pouring rain) and after 3 times to check and see if the food was ready. At last the food was done cooking. No apology, no offer of a free beef patty, not even a drink. I get home and expected to be "Delighted" in my tropical dish and the first thing we noticed was dry plantains. How  do you mess that up??    The oxtails need to be cooked longer as I was unable to bite, pull or chew on the undercooked meat  (that took me 2 hours to get) 

I like to support small business especially since we are in a time that many  businesses are losing money. We even took a menu in hopes to reorder food in the future and share it with friends. 

When we called to talk to the manager to explain our frustration about the long wait and the fact that the food wasnt even cooked properly they laughed and said sorry we can offer you a free plate. Why would I want more of the same? Or even risk get your extra special sauce included with my next meal? 

Please save your money, go on pinterest,  call a friend make your own food as it would come out faster and taste better then the food that is cooked here. 

Glad I own a pressure cooker, I'll see if I'm able to save my $40 meal.

I waited 30 mins for my order and it wasn’t even a busy time. The people are not even friendly at all. They don’t greet you, they don’t smile, they look miserable and they don’t care period! At least let your customers know if there’s going to be a delay on your order right? But of course they won’t. They just take your money and make you wait. Didn’t I say they don’t care? 

So when my food came, they did not apologize for the wait and it was not even hot. I expect that it would be pipping hot because it might be freshly cooked. That might explain my wait but it’s not. My food came drenched in sauce but it was mostly bones with very little meat. This for $16.99 are you kidding me? Look at the photo attached. What a horrible experience and a complete waste of money! DO NOT GO! The one in Loockerman street is way better!
The food is Caribbean style soul food they have lots of great things on the menu. We have used them for catering events. Stop by and pay then a visit it will be well worth your trip

I love the fried chicken and the fried whiting fish. The mac& cheese is very moist with cheese & flavor. The greens are not watered down. Yams and potato pies are very good. There are a storyteller of prices portions are ok only cause you could do much more. The beef patties and tropical food is delicious also. Papa & Mama be breaking it down they be burning “ Mr. Dave is keeping it moving and smooth. It’s well worth driving to the other side of town for, go and spend  $ 6 to 12 filling $.

I ordered the ox tails, rice & peas, cabbage with a side of mac & cheese.  This was my 1st purchase. Disappointed that the cabbage was over cooked, very soft. The serving of mac & cheese was an extremely small portion which I paid $3.75 for but only worth 50 cents. It  was dry/hard and and seemed to be leftover scraped from day old pan. The rice was mushy. The rice was mushy. I have been to Jamaica many times and ordered from a number of restaurants in this country.  Worst ever. I know what I should be getting.

name: The Brick-Wood Fired Eats
address: 150 Gateway S Blvd, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Was good. A few people got burnt pizza, but what I got when it finally came out was pretty tasty. I got the cicliano pizza, and the bacon wrapped jalapeno poppers. They didn't have many people there, but food came out randomly and slowly so sharing appetizers was kinda awkward. The pizza menu could have a few more options, but it was good nevertheless.
First time there it was great, food was delicious. Service was great.

My wife and I love this place, they make a good drink and the food is awesome. They make the best deviled eggs we have ever tasted. The staff is professional, the food is great and the atmosphere is comfortable.

The Brick was a true gastronomic treat! Normally not a huge fan of meatballs, I ordered the meatball appetizer and they were a true treat for the taste buds! I was in a party of five, and everyone's meal was excellent. As an added bonus, we were treated to live music in the form of Tim Jaudon for our Saturday evening meal. Please sign me up for more!
Food was delicious and a LOT of it!! You definitely won't leave hungry. 😊

name: Angelo's Pizza
address: 20 W Loockerman St, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: I really enjoyed their food. I always get awesome customer service there. The place is neat and the employees are always helpful. Keep up the good work.
When your feeling down on a Monday cause its Monday ,Angelo's is always there to have a nice joke and a great tasting pizza and the wings are awesome as well ,I love lemon pepper
Satisfyingly thin pizza with the proper ratio of cheese to sauce. Crisp yet chewy crust. Fantastic.
Customer service is really good... the food is good the delivery time is also expectacular
Wow this is the most amazing place. Best calzone ever created.

name: Pie Five Pizza
address: 1211 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: My first visit. I was impressed. I ordered a pie with pepperoni and meatballs. Came out fast and was good. I am not sure I love it yet. Will enjoy discovering more.
You can make an awesome pizza by selecting all the ingredients you would like to have put on it. The price is very reasonable. The staff is friendly and helpful.
Great fresh made pizza! Lots of options to choose from.  Pizza is made right in front of you! It's like a Subway but they make pizza!
My first visit and not too bad. Puts you in mind of a Subway. Best thing, it's quick and inexpensive.
Thin crust wasnt as crispy as expected and the person creating our pizza had ear buds in and could barely hear us. Toppings were very good too

name: The Lobby House
address: 9 E Loockerman St, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: Good food clean area.
Great bartender
Good Food and Atmosphere
Love the wings and Thursday night Mexican specials.
Good wings!

name: Roma Pizza
address: 1047 Walker Rd, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: Always great!  We order several times a week at work and it is always good.  Great salads, pizza and the wings are so good.  You won't be disappointed.  Also, everyone there is super pleasant and nice.  They really treat their customers good.
