Just do it. One of the few places that deliver on base and man it was good!!! Food was nice and hot. We got the philly cheese steaks and they were BOMB, you also get a TON of fries! We will be a repeat customer!

Great food , everything there delicious. My favorite is the grilled chicken sandwich lunch special with a Cesar salad instead of fries. But there fries are good too. Also, buffalo chicken pizza is the best I ever had

I never knew this little hidden gem existed! Its tucked away in a corner and I happened to stumble upon it one day.  The pizza and cheesesteak was good!  You can tell the pizza is made fresh.  The staff are also very friendly.
Staff was very helpful and friendly. Everything was good... Prompt service... Good people and good food👍👍

name: La Baguette Bakery and Catering
address: 323 S Governors Ave, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: Such a rare delight here in Dover. We lucked upon Customer Appreciation Day, and enjoyed samples of their chocolate salted caramel cake. I had the sausage, egg and cheese sandwich on the frontage roll. So good! Cheeses. Baked goods. Great coffee. Sandwiches. We will be back.

Amazing food. Always fresh, and consistently prepared. I frequently rely on their bakery for cakes, and enjoy the opportunity to meet friends there for lunch. Have also experienced events catered by La Baguette, which have been fantastic. Can always count on them to be organized with your orders as well.

Wonderful slice of France in downtown Dover. Truly our family happy place. We love to enjoy the pleasant atmosphere and quality food and warm smiles coupled with great service. From catering to cupcakes they can accommodate virtually anything. Just call them and see what they are able to do for you.

Incredible staff that are warm and friendly! Fresh delicious baked goods! You can’t go wrong with this bakery it’s high quality and good pricing! They will exceed your expectations and give you a new spot to hang out for a bit!

Lovely ❤️ Such a friendly staff, warm atmosphere and delicious food! I highly recommend the parisien chicken croissant sandwich, and literally anything from the bakery case. Though, I am partial to the chocolate chip cookies 😉  Gets a little busy at lunch, but very worth the wait for the freshly made on site food with no preservatives.

name: Chipotle Mexican Grill
address: 1141 N Dupont Hwy #101, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: I go to this marvelous  place from time to time since I like the good mood that is unique to this restaurant. The staff is very attentive and professional. The service is absolutely fast. Most important, the food they prepare is highly distinguished. I frequent more than once and I was always pleased. The payment is fair. I suggest this place to to everybody.

DONT order from them! My food was packaged carelessly, everything out and open, two separate bags of chips (open) my food was smashed and almost 30 min late getting here (all 3 bags wrinkled like they’ve been opened multiple times) . A total waste of money as I can’t eat it! With all that’s going on with this pandemic you would think their costumers health would be top priority, how can you not secure people’s food for transport!?  I’m totally disgusted, not to mention the 4 phone calls and no answer 🤬 and she Handed me my sauce 😳🤢

So my husband I were traveling and put in a mobile order for what we thought was this Chipotle. Turns out I’m quite directionally challenged, and had chosen the wrong Chipotle. We were almost an hour from the one I had chosen, so I explained that to the staff who kindly got us our order. I was super embarrassed, but the staff was so sweet and understanding. Also, the food was exceptional, by far the best Chipotle experience yet.
I’m glad Chipotle has lasted in Dover, DE for all these years. Delicious food and hard workers here. One of my favorite fast/casual food places!

This rating is for the single time we've ever ordered from this Chipotle via delivery. We ordered it at around 6:30PM, was assigned to be delivered at 7:11PM. It didn't arrive, and I attempted calling the business over 10 times, with 3 of those times going to voicemail. Assuming the business was closed, attempted to cancel the order and get a refund. Still nothing. At 8:45PM, after cooking a meal at home and eating, we recieved a knock at the door with cold Chipotle. It had a tag that had been written saying the order was ordered at 6:30PM and delivered at 7:00PM. 

We didn't receive our order at any reasonable time, was not notified of any delay, and there was still no communication from them. If I could, I would rate this as zero stars, as this is ridiculous! 

The only thing we want is a refund for an order that was over an hour and a half late and was colder than room temperature on arrival that we didn't need or want anymore. Tried calling to speak with a manager after we received the order, and yet again it went unanswered.

Update: was contacted by the corporation and was refunded the amount spent. Raised the Stars in the review to reflect this corporate service.

name: Friendly's - Delivery & Takeout Only
address: 318 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews:
This is my most favorite dessert ever.  Just wish there were more locations.
I do hit the one up in Orlando whenever we go.  Loved the one in Dover, De where I went at least once a month for this treat.

Food was great. Server was decent. We were overcharged for our soup and once it was corrected, we didn't realize we were then overcharged on the entree. I still like Friendly's and will be back. Will just check the receipt a lot closer. By the way, you can still get a military discount too.
Food was great and service was fast. I will visit again when in in Dover.  Loved our waitress .

Beware of the friendly's in Dover, DE ???? They have no clue on how to do a split check payment with two cards. Not only did they mess up the first time she wanted to swipe my card again without even deleting the first transaction and take more money. What in the world is going on????

The clam chowder was good, not overwhelming. The tunamelt was cold and the toasted bread was dry. A disappointment. I drove to Dover with the sole intention of experiencing local culture. I was not impressed. I have had far better "New England" clam chowder in California!

name: Boston Market
address: 1151 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews:
Fresh, nicely prepared food which is a great alternative to "fast food" restaurants. I always have a good experience when I come here. Restaurant is always clean and the staff is fast, friendly and accurate.

They have been expanding their menu and  now offer even more tasty food choices. The creamed.spinach is my all time favorite here. I also use Boston Market catering on occasion. Food is always ready on time, hot and the order is accurate and complete. The attention to detail exhibited by the staff here is what sets them apart.

You really can't beat the buy one get one free deal. The roast turkey is my go-to. It's always delicious, especially with some mashed potatoes and mac n cheese. The meat loaf is also decent. I like that you can order online and pick it up in 10 - 15 mins. They're always really fast.
It was an enjoyable experience and the food was very good. I was disappointed with the time and a accuracy of them taking my orders. The treatment of some patrons vic others was very noticeable.
The food was hot and fresh. The wait staff was courteous and the restaurant was clean and well maintained

First time going to this Boston Market location and the staff is very friendly and helpful. The food was fresh and everything they have for sides was there to pick from. Good cooking not fast food stop by and enjoy.

name: Big Daddy's Soul Food
address: 1030 S Little Creek Rd, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: This is the Medium Jamaican Curry Chicken with rice n peas with cabbage. Very good

The food here has flavor and cooked to perfection. I was not disappointed. We ordered the Ribs(highly recommend), White fish, hushpuppies, macaroni and cheese, along with sweet potato fries. Friendly customer service.

Love the food. If you're in a rush this isn't the place for you. The food can and will take some time getting out to you. I always get the spicy peach chicken wings with mac and cheese and yams(candied sweet potatoes).
WANTED TO ORDER FOR THE FIRST TIME AND HE DIDNT EVEN HAD WANT I WANTED AND HE CANCELLED MY FIRST ORDER BEFORE HE GOT IN CONTACT WITH ME!!!!
Good service and great food. The ribs taste sweet!

name: La Delicia Mexican Restaurant
address: 585 Forest St Ste 1, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews:
Parking was easy, the restaurant had plenty of spaces surrounding the building.
This is a small stand alone restaurant just off Rt 13, about 5 miles from the Air Force Base. The place was clean inside with many booths, and a few tables. The floor was slippery, like it was greased down. Be careful folks! Service was excellent, anything we needed, we had in a reasonable amount of time.

I ordered a bottled water to drink, cold, refeshing.

Chips & Salsa!!!
Chips...good flavor, a little on the stale side, but decent.
Salsa...the red had good fresh flavors, not as much cilantro as I like, and had a punch of fire for a few seconds. The green was fresh, refreshing, with a small touch of heat. I preferred the green and used it on everything.

I ordered chicken flautas: served with refried beans, rice, and salad.
The flautas were fried perfectly, chicken was seasoned well, moist, and tender. I prefer when they toss the salad on top of everything, and this salad was pretty lacking in size for 5 taquitos.
Beans...almost a soupy consistency, tasted good, solid refried bean game.
Rice...sticky, a bit dry, but serviceable. Mix them both to make it all right.

I ordered tacos choosing chorizo, lengua, and steak. They were out of pastor, so I was a bit sad.
Chorizo...wow!!! excellent char, melt in your mouth, flavor explosion. This was my fav chorizo taco on the journey so far. Outstanding!!!
Lengua...cut into small cubes, seasoned well, just wasn't doing it for me today. The green salsa helped me get though the couple bites I took. I'm hit or miss on the tongue, not today.
Steak...seasoned flawlessly, not too salty, you can taste the steak, and wasn't dry at all. The tortillas were good and had a little crunch to them.

I ordered a pork tamale.
It was wrapped in a banana leaf and had some of the fire red sauce in with the pork and masa. It was ok...quite dry, and the red sauce made it less enjoyable. Not my kind of tamale.

I ordered a carnitas sope.
I enjoyed it. The meat had excellent flavor, and a solid mix of meat to fat ratio. It could've used more refried beans spread on the tortilla. I used my beans, and it was much better. The tortilla was a little tougher than I prefer, but was still pretty dang good.

So yeah, La Delicia makes me think "delicious". Except not in reality.

The counter person was not personable at all, shading towards unfriendly. 
As for the food:  for starters, too much salt in their cooking. Salt should enhance and no more.  They went a bit heavy.

We had chicken, steak, carnitas, and lengua tacos The lengua was a bit tough and gamey.  The carnitas was fine, wife disliked the chicken and steak was okay.

There was also a burrito that should have been pork, but was chicken. 

The chicken tamale was not good at all, and went unfinished.

We asked for both the red and green salsa, 2 small containers were provided.  (picture enclosed) The red had decent spice, green was flavorful.

Lastly was the grease....ye gods, was this greasy. (pic enclosed showing some)

Some people liked this place, so maybe our experience was an aberration.  I won't chance it.

I love their enchiladas the only thing I wish is that they be more helpful to people not familiar to authentic mexican. I know I look like I could be spanish, but I'm not. Feel like your expected to know the menu already.

This place is on point. The food was incredibly good.  It had great flavor, good portions for the money as well.  I had the tacos; al pastor, chorizo, & lingua as well as the chicken tamale and the fried plantains.
Delicious food! The staff is friendly and welcoming.  I was introduced to their pineapple juice that they make fresh with a few other fruits   I'd come back just for a large cup of that!

name: Cobblestone Cafe
address: 408 S State St, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: I think the best gyros in Dover can be found here. The coffee is also very good. This place definitely deserves 5 stars. The food is great and the staff is amazing.

Very hole in the wall feeling! Seating for around 10 but from reading other reviews is seems many people take it to-go.

I had an omlet, which was very tasty! Reminded me of home cooking.

Would suggest stopping by if you are looking for something unique. Not expensive at all.

Cobblestone Cafe is a very quaint restaurant. It is located at The Green in Dover DE which is full of rich history. It is run by its owner and there is a steady stream of business from the local offices. Most customers take their food to go but there is a tiny place to sit and eat which is recommended if you can. If only to watch the people come in and out. The food is tasty. A fun place to visit.

Tiny hidden gem. Excellent  service, fresh, tasty food, and super cheap too! Charming decor with dolls, tea sets, and nick nacks.

Details: it is tiny as it can only seat about 8-10 people.) Small menu that includes breakfast (omelettes and bagels) and lunch (hot dog (beef frank), grilled cheese, a few sandwhiches.) Good coffee. Great service.
Had the falafel sandwich and it was delicious.

name: Giacomo's Party Room
address: 63 Greentree Dr, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: Been friends with the owners and other staff for years. Decent food and prices. Filling.
Great place to gather for pizza!
Great cheesesteaks.
The food is always well made, tasty, and authentic
This is very good

name: Pizzadili
address: 2089 S Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews:
The best subs in the country and everything they have is good. Cant beat it. And I'm talking for the 
last 30 plus years!  The best.
Place has been here since I remember. Awesome food and great people!
The food is constantly well prepared and tasty, cashiers provides excellent service. I love how neat it is and ambience. Will visit here again.

I've always loved Pizzadili as the quality of their food has been second to none. However, last night we ordered a pizza for the first time. It was pretty bad. I'm  certain it is prepackaged with a biscuit-like crust and mediocre sauce. It was so bad that I think they should take pizza off their menu. Now their subs and sandwiches have always been really delicious. But maybe last night was truly an off night. I ordered a cheeseburger sub. It was all roll and very little meat and no cheese!! Add-ons were meager: a little bit of lettuce, a few thin slices of tomato, hardly any onion and a light spread of mayo on the roll. It was the driest, dullest sub I've ever had. I had to doctor the second half of it. So disappointing.

This place has the best rice pudding in existence.  My mother couldn't make hers as good ad theirs. Also their pizzadeli special (Italian) sub is the best I have ever eaten. I highly recommend this sub shop.

name: The Brunch n Lunch
address: 212 S Governors Ave, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: We saw this online and saw the awesome menu and pictures of the food and environment. Well apparently they moved 8 months ago from that location and changed the menu. It took an hour for me to get a breakfast sandwich. They had live music which was cool but was way to loud for the tiny restaurant. It actually hurt my ears. Though the band was extremely talented. The food was good however they forget the cheese which is a dollar more. The menu is completely different that what’s online. There’s half as many items and the price is literally double. My meal online was $5.50 and in there was $9. It also appeared to be under construction as it was pretty junky. What you see online is completely opposite from what’s actually there. I’d give it another chance if the goal it to restore to what they use to have that was giving them so many positive reviews. I give 2 stars as the food was great. Also it wasn’t busy when we went. We were the only ones who didn’t have food and it still took an hour which doesn’t make sense.
We all know Dover isnt that great, but if you are craving a bite to eat..please take the time to fill up here. This is the place. The food, the atmosphere, and the people.

Very clean restaurant and staff is very friendly. This was my first time trying grits and my server went out of his way to explain what grits were like. Additionally, the restaurant was very clean and aesthetically pleasing with art made by local artists. Highly recommend others check it out!

Great food, and cool events. 

Out of most of the places downtown, The BnL seems to be one of the few trying to cultivate a homegrown art scene. They have a open mic reading series, occasional music acts and art work for sale on all the walls. I wish them luck because it's a great endeavor!
Incredible food! From the perfectly seasoned home fries to the equally impressive and delicious Brunch and Lunch burger, this is a must go restaurant when in Dover.

name: Glasgow Deli
address: 3920 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews:
This should be a 4.5.

The place makes good cheesesteaks. The big issue was having enough cheese.  I had mine with Swiss instead of American, as AMERICAN IS NOT CHEESE!!! That being said, it was hard to tell that there was cheese on the sandwich. But it was very tasty.

The bacon/broccoli bites (picture attached) weer also very nice. 

The place itself is very no-frills and the crowd skewed very old-white people. 

Definitely will return!

The owner of this establishment needs customer service skills. My order was messed up twice and they rufused to return my money for there mistake! Yelled and embarrassed me in front of other customers. 🤦🏽‍♂️ No professionalism!!
They serve large dishes and for reasonable prices. nice staff. 5 stars from me.

Love the goodies and especially the service at Glasgow Deli, our "go to" when we are out and about. All the servers make us feel like family. I can even special order my favorite! Cheeseburger topped with bacon and egg on whole wheat toast with a little mayo. 
The only neg is that they're not open Sundays, but I know they need family time too!
Good food. I had the cordon blue but without any dressing. The roll was fresh and soft.

name: MOD Pizza
address: 1037 N Dupont Hwy, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews:
Five stars for a five-star experience! I want to give a huge shout out of appreciation to the Dover MOD Pizza team.
 
This evening my family utilized their online ordering services. The system was incredibly user-friendly, and the in-house service was equally as excellent. The experience exceeded all expectations for a casual pizza dinner - the pizzas were delicious and prepared without error (something that seems to be a difficult task for most).
 
It's important to note that the restaurant was bustling when I came to pick up my order. However, despite the rush, the team made it a point to welcome me as I entered the restaurant warmly, and their customer service never gave way to the crowd. It's the little things that create a great experience.
 
Kudos to the team and their management, who cultivate an environment where excellent customer service is a priority for their team. Keep up the GREAT work!

First time at Mod pizza and it was great.  Nice decor and very clean.  Staff were friendly and engaging, and patient with the kids ordering.  Pizza was really good, cooked in a real oven not on a conveyor.  We'll definitely be back.

Place was amazing.  I was so happy with the service and the price.  We had the cauliflower crust and it was mind blowing.  It is our favorite pizza place to eat in Dover.   We have been going to Mod pizza since June and we have never been disappointed.
I stop here a lot between my shift at work but good pizza and it doesnt take too long to cook
Great pizza, fast service and the employees are always nice and friendly.

name: Wayback Burgers
address: 645 S Bay Rd RT 113, Dover, DE 19901, USA
reviews: If your in to burgers this is the spot. I loved the cheesssy. With flipped buns. The milkshake was overwhelming. I feel as though the cookies overpowered it. The cashier needs improvement her attitude was a bit overworked. Seeming that she didn't want to be there. I could be wrong. The cook always greets and presentation was on point. He was a black ma'am with pretty eyes. Maybe some music would help the dead vibe in the restaurant. But the food is amazing.
Great tasting burgers. Fries and tater tots taste great. My family loved it. I would eat here again. The place is nice and clean.
Love this place great food and staff definitely recommend to anyone

Food quality is always good.It's really 3.5 stars. It loses stars because when I order online for a specific time, I always have to wait past the time requested. Plus, the interior is dingy. 

1. Get the online ordering out on time consistently and it'll be 4.5 stars.
2. Renovate the interior and it'll be 5 star.

Giving it a 3 star because my fries were great and the actual burger was good...if you can get past the burnt bread taste. Literally tasted the burnt taste through the entire sandwich, couldn’t finish it-

name: Romano's Pizza & Restaurant
address: 768 Walker Rd, Dover, DE 19904, USA
reviews: This is a perfect blend of Italian and Mexican dishes.  I don't know if I've ever been to a place with such diverse menu options.  However this restaurant isn't the best choice if you looking for a sit down restaurant as their clientele is more for take out

Really good pizza, one of the best in Dover.  They sell by the slice and have several different unconventional to choose from.  Give it a try!

2015-9-21. Ordered a taco pizza, which isn't on menu, with refried beans, ground beef, cheese, lettuce tomato, hot taco sauce.  YUM!

2018-08-23. Got the Taco Pizza again with the green and red hot sauce...AWESOME!!!
All of the food we ordered was amazing! Great Italian and Mexican. Definitely our new favorite spot.
I absolutely love this place.  The Italian food is excellent and the Mexican food is awesome. Service is friendly.. the food is always prepared quickly and fresh and hot.
Best authentic tacos I've had.
